1
00:00:14,014 --> 00:00:16,483
<i>It's finally the day of the big match.</i>

2
00:00:16,549 --> 00:00:19,519
<i>Previously, Won-hun had to make a decision</i>

3
00:00:19,586 --> 00:00:21,654
<i>for our first and second rounds.</i>

4
00:00:21,721 --> 00:00:25,859
<i>Because Won-hun sided</i>
<i>with Chef Eun-yeong in both rounds,</i>

5
00:00:25,925 --> 00:00:28,461
she has now made it to the third round.

6
00:00:28,528 --> 00:00:31,097
She'll fight against Chef Ho-young
in the semifinals,

7
00:00:31,164 --> 00:00:33,600
who finished second in the regular season.

8
00:00:33,666 --> 00:00:34,567
It's a huge match.

9
00:00:34,634 --> 00:00:35,935
It's going to be so fun.

10
00:00:36,002 --> 00:00:37,570
The winner of that round

11
00:00:37,637 --> 00:00:40,373
will fight against
first-place Chef Choi Hyun-suk,

12
00:00:40,440 --> 00:00:44,310
who finished first in the regular season.

13
00:00:44,377 --> 00:00:48,214
<i>Who will be the champion</i>
<i>of the 2025 season…</i>

14
00:00:48,281 --> 00:00:51,217
-<i>I'm getting a headache.</i>
-<i>…of</i> Chef & My Fridge<i>?</i>

15
00:00:51,785 --> 00:00:54,054
COMING RIGHT UP

16
00:00:54,921 --> 00:00:57,223
We're here today with the two
variety show champions of 2025,

17
00:00:57,290 --> 00:01:00,026
Kim Won-hun and Lee Su-ji.

18
00:01:00,093 --> 00:01:01,861
This year, Su-ji won many awards.

19
00:01:01,928 --> 00:01:05,365
<i>The Grand Award</i>
<i>at the Korea First Brand Awards,</i>

20
00:01:05,432 --> 00:01:08,468
<i>the Celebrity YouTuber of the Year</i>
<i>and the Hottest Icon of the Year</i>

21
00:01:08,535 --> 00:01:10,437
<i>at the Brand of the Year Awards,</i>

22
00:01:10,503 --> 00:01:14,307
<i>and the Ministerial Commendation at the</i>
<i>Korea Popular Culture and Arts Awards.</i>

23
00:01:14,874 --> 00:01:16,109
-She won everything.
-Above all,

24
00:01:16,176 --> 00:01:18,311
she became the first Korean entertainer

25
00:01:18,378 --> 00:01:19,779
<i>to win the Baeksang Arts Awards</i>

26
00:01:19,846 --> 00:01:23,983
and the Blue Dragon Series Awards
in the same year.

27
00:01:25,018 --> 00:01:26,953
-Congratulations on your awards.
-Thank you.

28
00:01:27,020 --> 00:01:28,888
CONGRATULATIONS

29
00:01:29,155 --> 00:01:30,990
2025 WAS UNDOUBTEDLY SU-JI'S YEAR

30
00:01:31,057 --> 00:01:32,959
And I was there with her.

31
00:01:33,526 --> 00:01:34,661
<i>I was next to her.</i>

32
00:01:34,727 --> 00:01:36,496
<i>-You were nominated too.</i>
<i>-That's right.</i>

33
00:01:36,563 --> 00:01:38,531
-I celebrated with her.
-They're such good friends.

34
00:01:38,598 --> 00:01:39,766
How did that feel?

35
00:01:39,833 --> 00:01:41,101
These days,

36
00:01:41,167 --> 00:01:44,204
my mom calls me every morning and says,

37
00:01:44,270 --> 00:01:45,238
"Always be humble."

38
00:01:45,305 --> 00:01:46,940
<i>Be humble</i>

39
00:01:47,006 --> 00:01:49,209
She always says that
when everything starts to go to my head.

40
00:01:49,275 --> 00:01:50,743
LET US ALL STAY HUMBLE

41
00:01:50,810 --> 00:01:51,878
But honestly,

42
00:01:51,945 --> 00:01:54,180
I was only doing my job
just as I had all along.

43
00:01:54,247 --> 00:01:59,419
So I thought I was lucky this year
to have received all this attention.

44
00:01:59,486 --> 00:02:01,721
-She's so humble.
-It felt like people were bewitched,

45
00:02:01,788 --> 00:02:04,023
as if they'd even adore my poop.

46
00:02:04,090 --> 00:02:05,792
But I thought
that magic would wear off one day.

47
00:02:05,859 --> 00:02:07,193
QUIVERING EYES

48
00:02:07,260 --> 00:02:09,662
-I mean, I've always been the same.
-Look at him.

49
00:02:09,729 --> 00:02:11,331
Who the heck adores your poop?

50
00:02:12,499 --> 00:02:15,368
-I've never seen anyone like that.
-Let's not go that far.

51
00:02:15,435 --> 00:02:18,471
It was an analogy.
I felt like people adored me that much.

52
00:02:18,538 --> 00:02:21,541
One of the reasons
why Su-ji is loved by everyone

53
00:02:21,608 --> 00:02:23,176
is her ability to copy people.

54
00:02:23,243 --> 00:02:24,077
She gets possessed.

55
00:02:24,144 --> 00:02:27,113
-She copies their behaviors and attitudes.
-It's as if she's possessed.

56
00:02:27,180 --> 00:02:30,216
She once copied

57
00:02:30,283 --> 00:02:32,785
one of our chefs to a T.

58
00:02:32,852 --> 00:02:33,753
Let's take a look.

59
00:02:33,820 --> 00:02:35,822
-Who could it be?
-Who did Su-ji copy?

60
00:02:36,322 --> 00:02:37,157
LOOKING AWAY…

61
00:02:37,223 --> 00:02:38,124
They have the same eyes.

62
00:02:38,191 --> 00:02:40,260
-She's channeling him.
-They have the same dark circles.

63
00:02:40,326 --> 00:02:41,427
Is she his biological sister?

64
00:02:41,494 --> 00:02:43,163
When did you two do this together?

65
00:02:43,229 --> 00:02:46,466
We did that on <i>SNL Korea.</i>

66
00:02:46,533 --> 00:02:50,837
<i>I played him on the show</i>
<i>and got to pretend-cook with him.</i>

67
00:02:50,904 --> 00:02:54,040
There are many other chefs too.
What made you choose him?

68
00:02:54,107 --> 00:02:57,143
The way he stayed focused
while also being distracted was…

69
00:02:58,311 --> 00:02:59,712
SIMULTANEOUSLY FOCUSED AND DISTRACTED?

70
00:02:59,779 --> 00:03:02,382
Right? Focused and distracted.

71
00:03:02,448 --> 00:03:04,317
He was so focused, but at the same time,

72
00:03:04,384 --> 00:03:08,388
he was all over the place.
I get distracted like that too.

73
00:03:08,454 --> 00:03:11,090
So I thought I could copy his actions,

74
00:03:11,157 --> 00:03:13,259
and I actually had to practice
his restlessness.

75
00:03:13,893 --> 00:03:15,094
To bring out his character?

76
00:03:15,161 --> 00:03:20,099
So there must be facial expressions
and poses you probably practiced.

77
00:03:20,166 --> 00:03:23,603
Please go to the kitchen
and show us how well you can copy Nam-no.

78
00:03:24,170 --> 00:03:25,004
EXCITED

79
00:03:25,071 --> 00:03:26,439
There was a behavior that she noticed.

80
00:03:26,506 --> 00:03:28,374
-I can't watch.
-She's so shy until she begins.

81
00:03:28,675 --> 00:03:29,509
HAPPENS TO HAVE FRONT ROW SEATS

82
00:03:29,576 --> 00:03:30,610
I'll go.

83
00:03:30,677 --> 00:03:32,178
She'll show us Chef Nam-no.

84
00:03:32,245 --> 00:03:34,747
-Look at her face.
-Yes. It's Nam-no.

85
00:03:39,252 --> 00:03:41,054
FIDGETY FEET…

86
00:03:45,892 --> 00:03:47,160
DECALCOMANIA

87
00:03:48,061 --> 00:03:48,962
ADDING ANOTHER DETAIL

88
00:03:49,028 --> 00:03:50,663
-She's the same.
-That's it.

89
00:03:50,730 --> 00:03:52,665
SPRINKLING SALT

90
00:03:52,732 --> 00:03:54,634
-It's when he's cooking.
-Yes, he does that.

91
00:03:54,701 --> 00:03:56,469
-It feels like something's there.
-That's him.

92
00:03:56,536 --> 00:03:58,671
AS IF SHE HAD BEEN INSIDE HIM

93
00:03:59,439 --> 00:04:00,540
HUFF, WHEEZE

94
00:04:01,774 --> 00:04:03,343
A PERFECT FINISH

95
00:04:03,409 --> 00:04:04,944
She's just like him.

96
00:04:05,011 --> 00:04:07,280
-She copied him to a T.
-It's fascinating.

97
00:04:07,614 --> 00:04:08,815
AMAZED

98
00:04:08,881 --> 00:04:11,651
-That was amazing.
-She must study people a lot.

99
00:04:11,718 --> 00:04:12,585
NAM-NO'S TOWEL

100
00:04:12,652 --> 00:04:13,853
-Thanks, Su-ji.
-If you visit his restaurant,

101
00:04:13,920 --> 00:04:15,989
-he really does that.
-He does.

102
00:04:16,055 --> 00:04:19,892
I kept wondering what this was,
whenever she put her hands to her nose.

103
00:04:19,959 --> 00:04:21,127
-I wondered.
-When he gets nervous.

104
00:04:21,194 --> 00:04:24,597
-But he really does that.
-When I get nervous while getting judged.

105
00:04:24,664 --> 00:04:26,699
-He goes like this.
-He feels anxious.

106
00:04:26,766 --> 00:04:29,535
I was really impressed that day.

107
00:04:29,602 --> 00:04:33,039
She relentlessly puts in so much hard work

108
00:04:33,106 --> 00:04:35,508
to make people laugh hard…

109
00:04:35,575 --> 00:04:36,943
-She…
-He's already all over the place.

110
00:04:37,010 --> 00:04:39,445
-He's focused.
-It's because he's focused?

111
00:04:39,512 --> 00:04:42,615
As we just said, Su-ji fully absorbs
many of her multiple personas.

112
00:04:42,682 --> 00:04:44,917
-So we put together a clip of them.
-That sounds fun.

113
00:04:44,984 --> 00:04:46,519
-Let's take a look.
-It'll be fun.

114
00:04:47,954 --> 00:04:49,656
PERSONA ONE
GIRLIE GIRL DDU-JI

115
00:04:49,722 --> 00:04:51,057
<i>Girlie girl Ddu-ji.</i>

116
00:04:51,124 --> 00:04:54,260
I got snacky,
so I'll have some dried sweet potatoes.

117
00:04:54,327 --> 00:04:55,995
I feel like I know someone like her.

118
00:04:56,062 --> 00:04:57,497
She does seem like someone familiar.

119
00:04:57,563 --> 00:04:59,732
<i>That persona is supposed to be 48 kg.</i>

120
00:05:00,333 --> 00:05:03,436
HEAVE HO!

121
00:05:03,503 --> 00:05:04,504
Oh, my.

122
00:05:04,570 --> 00:05:05,405
She bent the spoon.

123
00:05:06,306 --> 00:05:07,573
-Is she supposed to be Uri Geller?
-It bent.

124
00:05:07,640 --> 00:05:09,309
URI GELLER'S SPOON

125
00:05:09,509 --> 00:05:10,710
PERSONA TWO
KOREAN-AMERICAN JENNY

126
00:05:10,777 --> 00:05:11,911
-Oh, Jenny.
-It's Jenny.

127
00:05:12,845 --> 00:05:15,281
AS IF SHE'S REALLY LIVED IN AMERICA

128
00:05:15,548 --> 00:05:16,616
PERSONA THREE
RAPPER HAMBUGGY

129
00:05:16,683 --> 00:05:18,851
-Hey, it's me, Hambuggy.
-She has so many personas.

130
00:05:20,420 --> 00:05:22,188
AMAZED

131
00:05:22,255 --> 00:05:24,624
You released a song,
performed in music shows,

132
00:05:24,691 --> 00:05:26,292
<i>and even went to the Waterbomb Festival.</i>

133
00:05:26,359 --> 00:05:28,695
EVEN OWNED THE WATERBOMB FESTIVAL

134
00:05:28,761 --> 00:05:31,631
-I went to the festival with her.
-He did.

135
00:05:31,698 --> 00:05:35,468
At first, she was dressed up nicely
as Hambuggy and got up to the stage.

136
00:05:35,535 --> 00:05:38,404
Then I saw her after the performance,

137
00:05:38,471 --> 00:05:39,472
a hippo…

138
00:05:41,708 --> 00:05:43,276
A HIPPO? COME ON…

139
00:05:43,343 --> 00:05:45,578
I mean, she was drenched.

140
00:05:45,645 --> 00:05:47,680
She was completely drenched.

141
00:05:47,747 --> 00:05:49,015
EXCUSE ME?

142
00:05:49,082 --> 00:05:52,318
-I realized she was so passionate.
-Jong-won broke out in laughter.

143
00:05:52,385 --> 00:05:55,421
Su-ji looks quite offended.
You can't just laugh like that.

144
00:05:55,488 --> 00:05:58,624
-We've never met before, have we?
-Actually, he really loves hippos.

145
00:05:58,691 --> 00:06:00,793
He's just really into hippos.

146
00:06:00,860 --> 00:06:03,930
He goes to the zoo
only to look at hippos, you know.

147
00:06:03,996 --> 00:06:05,398
-Please do understand.
-He adores them.

148
00:06:05,465 --> 00:06:06,532
-We've never even met.
-He's moved.

149
00:06:06,599 --> 00:06:08,267
-I really love hippos.
-He does.

150
00:06:08,334 --> 00:06:10,670
-That's why he's into me.
-I've always loved them.

151
00:06:10,737 --> 00:06:12,238
NO ONE CAN STOP HIS LOVE FOR HIPPOS

152
00:06:12,305 --> 00:06:14,807
-How much does he love hippos?
-He's even crying.

153
00:06:15,274 --> 00:06:16,409
WIPE YOUR TEARS

154
00:06:17,377 --> 00:06:18,378
Yes.

155
00:06:18,978 --> 00:06:22,749
As much as her persona, Hambuggy,
who shouts out to sexy food…

156
00:06:22,815 --> 00:06:24,217
That was excellent pronunciation.

157
00:06:24,283 --> 00:06:26,185
He's an announcer.

158
00:06:27,120 --> 00:06:28,755
That's how announcers make a living.

159
00:06:28,821 --> 00:06:31,924
Anyway, we confirmed that
she's also very serious about food.

160
00:06:31,991 --> 00:06:35,428
She's especially known as the genius
of the Certified Foodie Quiz.

161
00:06:35,495 --> 00:06:36,496
What's that?

162
00:06:36,562 --> 00:06:38,931
Do you all know
what the Certified Foodie Quiz is?

163
00:06:38,998 --> 00:06:41,267
-No, what's that? Certified Foodie?
-The Certified Foodie Quiz.

164
00:06:41,334 --> 00:06:43,436
<i>You try to guess what the food is</i>

165
00:06:43,503 --> 00:06:47,907
<i>by looking at an extremely zoomed-in photo</i>
<i>of the dish in question.</i>

166
00:06:47,974 --> 00:06:49,142
That sounds fun.

167
00:06:49,208 --> 00:06:52,311
Many of our chefs would also do well
on the Certified Foodie Quiz as foodies.

168
00:06:52,378 --> 00:06:53,312
We're certified foodies too.

169
00:06:53,379 --> 00:06:55,281
Would you like to challenge Su-ji on this?

170
00:06:55,348 --> 00:06:56,682
-Why don't we play together?
-Sure.

171
00:06:56,749 --> 00:06:59,552
-It's her versus the eight of you.
-One versus eight?

172
00:06:59,619 --> 00:07:01,921
Please show us the first picture.

173
00:07:03,289 --> 00:07:04,323
-Su-ji.
-Su-ji?

174
00:07:04,891 --> 00:07:07,059
SHE CAN TELL RIGHT AWAY?

175
00:07:07,126 --> 00:07:08,227
Half-dried saury?

176
00:07:08,294 --> 00:07:10,163
-Half-dried saury? No.
-What? Half-dried saury?

177
00:07:10,229 --> 00:07:11,164
-Nam-no.
-Nam-no?

178
00:07:11,230 --> 00:07:12,131
Acorn jelly.

179
00:07:12,198 --> 00:07:13,399
Acorn jelly?

180
00:07:13,466 --> 00:07:15,234
Are we looking at it through a microscope?

181
00:07:15,301 --> 00:07:16,969
You must say the dish's exact name.

182
00:07:17,036 --> 00:07:18,838
-Acorn jelly soup.
-Acorn jelly soup, correct!

183
00:07:19,539 --> 00:07:21,240
-That's acorn jelly soup?
-My gosh.

184
00:07:21,307 --> 00:07:22,809
-How is that acorn jelly soup?
-That's acorn jelly?

185
00:07:22,875 --> 00:07:24,977
<i>-We'll show you the whole photo.</i>
<i>-Isn't it a rice bowl?</i>

186
00:07:25,044 --> 00:07:27,079
Like that? How are we supposed to know?

187
00:07:27,146 --> 00:07:29,916
-That's cruel.
-We're showing you the zoomed-in version.

188
00:07:29,982 --> 00:07:32,151
-How did you know?
-The reflection was rough.

189
00:07:32,218 --> 00:07:33,453
-He got it right.
-That's amazing.

190
00:07:33,519 --> 00:07:35,154
It felt like there would be
<i>makgeolli</i> next to it.

191
00:07:35,221 --> 00:07:38,257
-He eats a lot.
-He knows a thing or two about food.

192
00:07:38,324 --> 00:07:39,892
Good one, Nam-no.

193
00:07:39,959 --> 00:07:41,761
Show us the second photo.

194
00:07:41,828 --> 00:07:42,962
-This is easier.
-I know.

195
00:07:43,029 --> 00:07:44,197
-Nam-no.
-Nam-no?

196
00:07:44,263 --> 00:07:45,331
-I know.
-Nam-no.

197
00:07:45,398 --> 00:07:46,866
-Nam-no?
-Tiramisu.

198
00:07:47,667 --> 00:07:49,602
-Tiramisu? Correct.
-I don't think so.

199
00:07:49,836 --> 00:07:51,137
TOOK HIM 1 SECOND

200
00:07:51,204 --> 00:07:53,806
-Take a break, Nam-no.
-How is that tiramisu?

201
00:07:53,873 --> 00:07:55,675
-I can tell everything.
-It's all in here.

202
00:07:55,741 --> 00:07:58,544
-How did he know?
-I thought it was a pork cutlet.

203
00:07:58,611 --> 00:08:00,480
-Me too.
-I thought it was a pork cutlet.

204
00:08:00,546 --> 00:08:02,248
-It looks good.
-Nam-no gets two points.

205
00:08:02,315 --> 00:08:04,283
There's a reason why he is this big.

206
00:08:04,350 --> 00:08:05,318
Show us.

207
00:08:06,619 --> 00:08:08,221
Su-ji.

208
00:08:08,287 --> 00:08:09,155
Su-ji.

209
00:08:09,555 --> 00:08:10,423
THAT QUICKLY?

210
00:08:10,490 --> 00:08:12,725
-<i>Mala</i> stir-fry.
-<i>Mala</i> stir-fry? Correct.

211
00:08:13,893 --> 00:08:15,461
I thought it was chicken feet at first.

212
00:08:15,528 --> 00:08:16,429
Stir-fry.

213
00:08:16,496 --> 00:08:18,664
-I should've said it right away.
-You got one.

214
00:08:18,731 --> 00:08:21,100
Su-ji is just getting started.

215
00:08:21,167 --> 00:08:22,768
We'll show you the last photo.

216
00:08:24,003 --> 00:08:25,771
-That's really hard.
-This is hard.

217
00:08:25,838 --> 00:08:27,206
-Su-ji.
-Su-ji?

218
00:08:27,273 --> 00:08:28,140
Sweet and sour pork?

219
00:08:28,207 --> 00:08:30,243
-Sweet and sour pork? No.
-I don't think so.

220
00:08:30,309 --> 00:08:32,278
-It looks so shiny.
-Wait, that's…

221
00:08:32,345 --> 00:08:33,412
Did you say shiny?

222
00:08:33,980 --> 00:08:35,181
-Is that a worm?
-Yes, it's shiny.

223
00:08:35,248 --> 00:08:36,349
SERIOUSLY?

224
00:08:36,415 --> 00:08:37,783
Nam-no. <i>Makchang</i>, grilled tripe.

225
00:08:37,850 --> 00:08:39,151
Su-ji. <i>Daechang</i>, beef large intestines.

226
00:08:39,218 --> 00:08:40,653
-<i>Makchang?</i> No.
-I know!

227
00:08:40,720 --> 00:08:42,088
-I know!
-Poong.

228
00:08:42,154 --> 00:08:44,423
-I'm sorry. I got it right.
-What is it?

229
00:08:44,490 --> 00:08:45,424
What is it?

230
00:08:46,993 --> 00:08:48,227
<i>Pho.</i>

231
00:08:48,294 --> 00:08:50,863
<i>-Pho? </i>No.
<i>-Pho?</i>

232
00:08:50,930 --> 00:08:51,831
No!

233
00:08:51,898 --> 00:08:52,899
WRONG

234
00:08:52,965 --> 00:08:55,034
-What's that thing?
-This one…

235
00:08:55,101 --> 00:08:56,469
-Nam-no.
-Nam-no?

236
00:08:56,536 --> 00:08:57,770
-Braised chicken feet.
-Braised chicken feet?

237
00:08:57,837 --> 00:09:00,039
-Correct!
-Are you serious?

238
00:09:00,106 --> 00:09:01,340
Seriously? Braised chicken feet?

239
00:09:01,407 --> 00:09:03,042
-Is that a thing?
-It was so hard.

240
00:09:03,109 --> 00:09:04,777
-What is that?
-I've never even heard of it.

241
00:09:04,844 --> 00:09:05,711
It looks so good.

242
00:09:05,778 --> 00:09:08,114
-I'm the piggy rep around here.
-She got only one.

243
00:09:08,180 --> 00:09:09,081
He knows his food.

244
00:09:09,148 --> 00:09:11,784
He guessed three correctly against Su-ji.

245
00:09:11,851 --> 00:09:15,922
-Nam-no becomes the certified foodie!
-Is this a good thing?

246
00:09:16,622 --> 00:09:17,757
I knew he'd come through.

247
00:09:18,724 --> 00:09:19,859
CONGRATS

248
00:09:19,926 --> 00:09:22,662
-This was why Su-ji copied Nam-no.
-He ate a lot for a reason.

249
00:09:22,728 --> 00:09:25,665
I guess the two certified foodies
have something in common.

250
00:09:25,731 --> 00:09:28,301
-What have I been eating all along?
-All right, then.

251
00:09:28,367 --> 00:09:31,070
And because Su-ji knows a lot about food,

252
00:09:31,137 --> 00:09:34,574
I'm sure she'll play
an important role in the championship.

253
00:09:34,640 --> 00:09:37,043
2025 <i>Chef & My Fridge</i> Championship.

254
00:09:37,109 --> 00:09:40,947
Today we have the long-awaited finals,

255
00:09:41,013 --> 00:09:43,049
and the biggest star of 2025,

256
00:09:43,115 --> 00:09:46,586
Lee Su-ji will decide everything.

257
00:09:46,652 --> 00:09:47,954
That's a lot of pressure.

258
00:09:48,020 --> 00:09:51,123
And now, allow me to share

259
00:09:51,190 --> 00:09:55,628
the final two matches we'll hold
with ingredients from Su-ji's fridge.

260
00:09:55,695 --> 00:09:58,965
Here are the two matches.

261
00:09:59,031 --> 00:10:01,934
Jung Ho-young and Park Eun-yeong
are in the semifinals,

262
00:10:02,001 --> 00:10:04,804
and the winner of that match
will move on to the finals,

263
00:10:04,870 --> 00:10:08,207
receiving a chance
to fight against Choi Hyun-suk.

264
00:10:08,274 --> 00:10:09,909
He's really like the final boss.

265
00:10:09,976 --> 00:10:12,545
-Is he asleep?
-I think he's asleep.

266
00:10:12,612 --> 00:10:13,980
Your side bangs are down too low.

267
00:10:14,046 --> 00:10:15,948
I think that's his thing today.

268
00:10:16,015 --> 00:10:17,083
SWOOSH

269
00:10:17,383 --> 00:10:18,784
LOVES HIMSELF TO DEATH

270
00:10:18,851 --> 00:10:22,488
First, here's the theme
for the semifinals.

271
00:10:22,555 --> 00:10:23,990
Show us the theme!

272
00:10:24,056 --> 00:10:25,458
Wow, Sexy Veggie.

273
00:10:25,524 --> 00:10:26,892
Veggie? That sounds tough.

274
00:10:26,959 --> 00:10:28,127
-Veggies?
-Veggies sound tough.

275
00:10:28,194 --> 00:10:29,362
<i>Wow, Sexy Veggie</i>

276
00:10:29,428 --> 00:10:32,131
<i>Wow, Sexy Veggie</i>

277
00:10:32,198 --> 00:10:33,232
Do you like veggies?

278
00:10:33,299 --> 00:10:34,200
I LOVE VEGGIES

279
00:10:34,266 --> 00:10:35,334
Do you like veggies?

280
00:10:35,401 --> 00:10:36,869
-Isn't that a big twist?
-Yes.

281
00:10:36,936 --> 00:10:38,971
But I really love vegetables.

282
00:10:39,038 --> 00:10:44,276
So I wondered what it would be like
to have these chefs make a veggie dish.

283
00:10:44,343 --> 00:10:46,345
I became curious.

284
00:10:46,412 --> 00:10:47,380
However,

285
00:10:47,446 --> 00:10:50,416
I don't really like it
if a dish is solely made of veggies.

286
00:10:50,483 --> 00:10:54,620
I want it to have
a bit of meat on the side.

287
00:10:54,687 --> 00:10:57,289
Would you prefer more veggies?

288
00:10:57,356 --> 00:10:59,358
-Well, how should I put this?
-Or about 50-50?

289
00:10:59,425 --> 00:11:01,127
-It should be more.
-Give us a ratio.

290
00:11:01,193 --> 00:11:02,328
In that case,

291
00:11:02,395 --> 00:11:04,263
please make sure
my dish has more meat then.

292
00:11:04,330 --> 00:11:06,699
-What? Then why is the theme veggies?
-That's just a meat dish.

293
00:11:06,766 --> 00:11:08,300
-That's Wow, Sexy Meat.
-It's sexy…

294
00:11:08,367 --> 00:11:09,935
-Sexy…
-Is it Sexy Meat?

295
00:11:10,002 --> 00:11:11,003
That's Sexy Meat.

296
00:11:11,070 --> 00:11:12,972
It's a huge twist,
but I really love vegetables.

297
00:11:13,039 --> 00:11:15,074
She does love veggies, though.

298
00:11:15,141 --> 00:11:17,643
When she was on a mono diet,

299
00:11:17,710 --> 00:11:18,844
she ate 40 cucumbers a day.

300
00:11:18,911 --> 00:11:20,513
-Cucumbers?
-Forty?

301
00:11:20,579 --> 00:11:22,748
-She loves veggies.
-In that case,

302
00:11:22,815 --> 00:11:25,184
it should be a mix of veggies and meat,
and the ratio…

303
00:11:25,251 --> 00:11:27,186
-Something reasonable.
-…should be reasonable.

304
00:11:27,253 --> 00:11:29,689
-But the main ingredients are veggies.
-Yes.

305
00:11:29,755 --> 00:11:31,223
Let's find out the second order.

306
00:11:31,290 --> 00:11:32,625
What is it for the finals?

307
00:11:32,692 --> 00:11:35,027
-The 2025 Final Match.
-The Final Match.

308
00:11:35,094 --> 00:11:36,228
-Open theme?
-Open theme?

309
00:11:36,295 --> 00:11:40,599
This is the final round
that'll decide the champion of 2025.

310
00:11:40,666 --> 00:11:42,635
-Yes.
-Because these will be the last dishes,

311
00:11:42,702 --> 00:11:44,870
I want you to put in everything you have

312
00:11:44,937 --> 00:11:47,940
-and make something delicious.
-So it's open-themed.

313
00:11:48,007 --> 00:11:49,642
You can make whatever you want,

314
00:11:49,709 --> 00:11:52,111
but the ingredients are limited.

315
00:11:52,178 --> 00:11:54,146
I can see the three chefs' eyes gleaming.

316
00:11:54,213 --> 00:11:57,516
Who will rise as the best chef?

317
00:11:57,583 --> 00:12:00,786
It's time to go through Su-ji's fridge,

318
00:12:00,853 --> 00:12:03,189
whose year 2025 has shined brightly.

319
00:12:03,255 --> 00:12:06,425
I hear you only take one day off
a month these days.

320
00:12:06,492 --> 00:12:08,994
-That's right. That's true.
-Really?

321
00:12:09,061 --> 00:12:10,896
How do you manage your fridge?

322
00:12:10,963 --> 00:12:13,032
I don't manage my fridge.

323
00:12:13,099 --> 00:12:16,135
I just eat stuff to get rid of it.

324
00:12:16,368 --> 00:12:17,937
THAT'S NEW

325
00:12:18,003 --> 00:12:21,974
My husband usually volunteers
to manage the fridge.

326
00:12:22,041 --> 00:12:23,542
Their house can't function

327
00:12:23,609 --> 00:12:26,645
-without her husband's help.
-That's so true.

328
00:12:26,712 --> 00:12:29,181
And he's been taking up the job.

329
00:12:29,248 --> 00:12:31,383
I wonder what ingredients she has.

330
00:12:31,450 --> 00:12:32,384
Let's find out!

331
00:12:33,486 --> 00:12:35,287
FOCUS MODE

332
00:12:35,354 --> 00:12:36,255
Let's find out!

333
00:12:36,322 --> 00:12:38,190
OH MY

334
00:12:38,257 --> 00:12:39,992
That's really my fridge.

335
00:12:40,059 --> 00:12:41,160
HAHAHAHA

336
00:12:41,961 --> 00:12:42,995
She has lots of stuff.

337
00:12:43,062 --> 00:12:44,396
THIS IS SU-JI'S FRIDGE

338
00:12:44,463 --> 00:12:47,399
-We present Su-ji's fridge.
-It's more organized than I thought.

339
00:12:47,466 --> 00:12:49,235
She has quite a lot of ingredients, right?

340
00:12:49,301 --> 00:12:51,203
Let us begin with the top shelf.

341
00:12:51,270 --> 00:12:54,073
She must be into these pickled vegetables.

342
00:12:54,140 --> 00:12:55,574
I see pickled green plums too.

343
00:12:55,641 --> 00:12:56,976
-I see.
-Do you enjoy these?

344
00:12:57,042 --> 00:12:58,511
Seems like it's her first time seeing it.

345
00:12:59,545 --> 00:13:00,679
Is that so?

346
00:13:00,746 --> 00:13:02,081
I see.

347
00:13:02,148 --> 00:13:04,016
FIRST TIME SEEING HER PICKLED VEGGIES

348
00:13:04,083 --> 00:13:05,951
It was all the way inside.

349
00:13:06,018 --> 00:13:07,119
It must be old.

350
00:13:07,186 --> 00:13:09,522
-Can you still eat that?
-Big time. It was pickled.

351
00:13:09,588 --> 00:13:11,991
-It's preserved.
-Big time? It sounded like "pig time."

352
00:13:12,057 --> 00:13:13,993
YOU CAN'T CALL HER A PIG

353
00:13:14,059 --> 00:13:16,729
-Please watch out.
-Big time.

354
00:13:16,796 --> 00:13:18,297
Organic lemon juice.

355
00:13:18,364 --> 00:13:19,965
-What?
-Four boxes of organic lemon juice.

356
00:13:20,032 --> 00:13:21,267
-How do you use this?
-It's good for you.

357
00:13:21,333 --> 00:13:24,336
That's the routine of an actress like me.

358
00:13:24,403 --> 00:13:25,871
-It's your routine?
-Yes.

359
00:13:25,938 --> 00:13:28,440
I wake up, yawn, rinse my mouth,

360
00:13:28,507 --> 00:13:32,311
and have a packet of olive oil.

361
00:13:32,378 --> 00:13:36,949
After that, I mix lemon juice
with some water and have a cup.

362
00:13:37,016 --> 00:13:39,185
That's how I keep my youthful looks.

363
00:13:39,251 --> 00:13:40,719
But I had to skip my routine today

364
00:13:40,786 --> 00:13:42,755
because I couldn't have my lemon juice.

365
00:13:42,822 --> 00:13:44,757
Because we took your fridge.

366
00:13:45,391 --> 00:13:47,660
-If you haven't had one, have one now.
-Yes, how do you take it?

367
00:13:47,726 --> 00:13:48,761
Have one.

368
00:13:48,828 --> 00:13:51,330
-This is… One moment.
-She said she mixes it with water.

369
00:13:51,397 --> 00:13:52,832
CHUG

370
00:13:54,867 --> 00:13:57,903
JUST WATCHING HER DRINK WATER
MAKES HIM HAPPY

371
00:13:58,170 --> 00:13:59,538
GLARE

372
00:13:59,605 --> 00:14:01,740
-Because she's like a hippo?
-Jong-won must be smitten.

373
00:14:02,942 --> 00:14:05,411
POURING

374
00:14:05,477 --> 00:14:07,680
It refreshes you in the morning.

375
00:14:07,746 --> 00:14:11,851
It feels like you can start your day
without any toxins in your body.

376
00:14:13,719 --> 00:14:14,920
With a pinky up.

377
00:14:15,621 --> 00:14:17,089
So that's her secret.

378
00:14:17,156 --> 00:14:19,458
You have to finish the whole thing.
Bottoms up.

379
00:14:19,525 --> 00:14:22,194
-"Bottoms up"?
-Do you have to do a bottoms up?

380
00:14:22,261 --> 00:14:24,096
-You'll get addicted to water.
-You can take a break.

381
00:14:24,163 --> 00:14:26,065
But you must finish the bottle.

382
00:14:26,131 --> 00:14:28,400
-Her morning routine.
-Right. You must use lukewarm water.

383
00:14:29,768 --> 00:14:32,605
-Cold water isn't good in the morning.
-Nothing too cold. Lukewarm water.

384
00:14:32,671 --> 00:14:34,807
And do you begin your meals with lunch?

385
00:14:34,874 --> 00:14:36,108
No, after I drink this,

386
00:14:36,175 --> 00:14:37,610
I eat Greek yogurt.

387
00:14:37,676 --> 00:14:40,646
First, I soak blueberries
in running water.

388
00:14:40,713 --> 00:14:43,382
Then about seven Greek yogurts…

389
00:14:43,449 --> 00:14:46,118
-Seven Greek yogurts?
-No, blueberries.

390
00:14:46,185 --> 00:14:47,887
SHE WOULDN'T, LOL

391
00:14:47,953 --> 00:14:50,589
So you caught me with one mistake.

392
00:14:50,656 --> 00:14:53,158
Anyway, I mix it
with about seven blueberries.

393
00:14:53,225 --> 00:14:56,128
-Blueberries and Greek yogurt.
-Yes, that's my breakfast.

394
00:14:56,195 --> 00:14:58,564
-That's how I eat it too.
-I see.

395
00:14:58,631 --> 00:15:00,266
Is there anything you don't eat?

396
00:15:00,332 --> 00:15:02,902
I'm not really into sweet food.

397
00:15:02,968 --> 00:15:04,837
-Sweet food?
-I don't have much of a sweet tooth.

398
00:15:04,904 --> 00:15:07,139
One shelf below has bread.

399
00:15:07,206 --> 00:15:09,842
I see strawberry jam here.
Do you eat this with jam?

400
00:15:09,909 --> 00:15:12,344
There's another routine I have.

401
00:15:12,411 --> 00:15:14,713
-You said you didn't like sweet things.
-That's really sweet.

402
00:15:14,780 --> 00:15:16,982
I don't prefer my bread
with strawberry jam.

403
00:15:17,049 --> 00:15:18,050
It's peanut butter.

404
00:15:18,117 --> 00:15:20,286
-Peanut butter.
-That's sweet too.

405
00:15:20,352 --> 00:15:22,021
-I found it.
-That's my spread.

406
00:15:22,087 --> 00:15:25,658
I like to toast the bread
and spread peanut butter on it.

407
00:15:25,724 --> 00:15:27,660
It makes me so happy.

408
00:15:27,726 --> 00:15:29,128
I KNOW THAT FEELING

409
00:15:29,194 --> 00:15:31,530
You seem to eat a lot in the morning.

410
00:15:31,931 --> 00:15:34,166
HAS QUITE AN APPETITE EARLY IN THE DAY

411
00:15:34,233 --> 00:15:36,535
-Every shelf is full of breakfast foods.
-It's because

412
00:15:36,602 --> 00:15:38,570
we're supposed to eat seven nuts a day.

413
00:15:38,637 --> 00:15:42,174
But I never get around to doing that,
so I eat peanut butter instead.

414
00:15:42,241 --> 00:15:44,710
You'll have to wake up at 3 a.m.
to eat your breakfast.

415
00:15:44,777 --> 00:15:45,878
That's her routine.

416
00:15:45,945 --> 00:15:48,280
I hope the three chefs
continue to listen carefully.

417
00:15:48,347 --> 00:15:51,317
Do you eat healthy at home,
especially for breakfast?

418
00:15:51,383 --> 00:15:53,686
I usually have to eat

419
00:15:53,752 --> 00:15:56,789
my lunch and dinner outside while working,

420
00:15:56,855 --> 00:15:59,358
so I wanted to eat
something healthier in the morning

421
00:15:59,425 --> 00:16:01,493
and start my day like that.

422
00:16:01,560 --> 00:16:03,128
Do you eat Korean food for lunch?

423
00:16:03,195 --> 00:16:04,797
I like to eat <i>sundae-guk.</i>

424
00:16:04,863 --> 00:16:05,898
And for dinner?

425
00:16:05,965 --> 00:16:08,534
Dinner? Ox bone <i>haejang-guk</i>

426
00:16:08,600 --> 00:16:10,669
or maybe pork belly.

427
00:16:10,736 --> 00:16:12,204
Lamb skewers.

428
00:16:12,271 --> 00:16:13,806
-Chicken feet.
-At least her breakfast is healthy.

429
00:16:13,872 --> 00:16:16,008
-<i>Sundae-guk</i>, chicken feet,
-<i>Sundae-guk.</i>

430
00:16:16,075 --> 00:16:19,244
-<i>Malatang</i>. Something like that.
-<i>Jokbal, mala</i> soup.

431
00:16:19,311 --> 00:16:22,147
Are the lyrics to "Sexy Food"
all autobiographical?

432
00:16:22,214 --> 00:16:23,582
I love them all.

433
00:16:23,649 --> 00:16:25,017
-It was about her.
-Yes.

434
00:16:25,084 --> 00:16:27,686
-It's her story, except for sweets.
-My inspirations.

435
00:16:27,753 --> 00:16:29,588
-We already had all the hints.
-Yes.

436
00:16:29,655 --> 00:16:31,423
And the crisper drawer.

437
00:16:31,490 --> 00:16:33,525
-The main ingredient of the day.
-That's a lot.

438
00:16:33,592 --> 00:16:35,260
It's so full.

439
00:16:35,327 --> 00:16:37,796
There are lots of mushrooms.

440
00:16:37,863 --> 00:16:40,199
-Spinach. Napa cabbage.
-Napa cabbage.

441
00:16:40,265 --> 00:16:41,400
Lettuce.

442
00:16:41,467 --> 00:16:42,968
-I like them.
-Look at this lettuce.

443
00:16:43,302 --> 00:16:45,371
HIGHLY INTERESTED

444
00:16:45,437 --> 00:16:48,340
-Do you enjoy bean sprouts?
-I love bean sprouts.

445
00:16:48,407 --> 00:16:50,909
I love veggies like bean sprouts
and mung bean sprouts.

446
00:16:50,976 --> 00:16:54,179
Ho-young and Eun-yeong will fill the order
for Wow, Sexy Veggie,

447
00:16:54,246 --> 00:16:55,881
and there are lots of them here.

448
00:16:55,948 --> 00:16:58,984
The very last drawer has fruit.

449
00:16:59,051 --> 00:17:02,488
I see apples,
and you must love persimmons.

450
00:17:02,554 --> 00:17:06,191
My father-in-law has a cucumber farm
in Gurye, South Jeolla-do.

451
00:17:06,258 --> 00:17:08,727
And there, no one buys persimmons

452
00:17:08,794 --> 00:17:11,096
because everyone has a tree.

453
00:17:11,163 --> 00:17:15,534
He'd pick the soft persimmons
and send us boxes of them.

454
00:17:15,601 --> 00:17:18,337
-He must adore his daughter-in-law.
-He does.

455
00:17:18,404 --> 00:17:20,372
-You're so blessed.
-She is.

456
00:17:20,439 --> 00:17:21,874
This side is the freezer.

457
00:17:21,940 --> 00:17:24,510
I'm starting to see some meat.

458
00:17:24,576 --> 00:17:26,211
-She has a lot of meat.
-Yes.

459
00:17:26,278 --> 00:17:28,714
There's beef, and this must be pork.

460
00:17:28,781 --> 00:17:31,283
Which do you prefer? Beef or pork?

461
00:17:31,350 --> 00:17:32,518
Both.

462
00:17:32,584 --> 00:17:33,652
-Both?
-Yes.

463
00:17:33,719 --> 00:17:36,255
I'd eat pork for about five days,

464
00:17:36,321 --> 00:17:39,024
and eat beef on the two remaining days.

465
00:17:39,091 --> 00:17:41,093
Do you eat meat at least once a day?

466
00:17:41,160 --> 00:17:43,729
I almost always eat meat for dinner.

467
00:17:43,796 --> 00:17:45,898
WHETHER THE DAYS WERE GREAT OR NOT,
I ALWAYS ATE MEAT…

468
00:17:45,964 --> 00:17:48,300
-She really loves meat.
-She does.

469
00:17:48,367 --> 00:17:51,070
The next shelf has some fish.

470
00:17:51,136 --> 00:17:53,238
-I see some cutlassfish.
-That's rare.

471
00:17:53,305 --> 00:17:55,607
And some tiny abalones.

472
00:17:55,674 --> 00:17:57,109
What's this?

473
00:17:57,676 --> 00:18:00,012
Freshwater snail meat?

474
00:18:00,079 --> 00:18:02,948
Yes, they're freshwater snails.
I love them.

475
00:18:03,615 --> 00:18:07,019
-It's the texture, so for <i>doenjang-jjigae,</i>
-Freshwater snail <i>doenjang-guk?</i>

476
00:18:07,086 --> 00:18:09,254
I put in about this much at once.

477
00:18:10,122 --> 00:18:15,427
I like to scoop up a spoonful
and make a lettuce wrap with <i>ssamjang.</i>

478
00:18:15,494 --> 00:18:17,396
It's so good. Argh.

479
00:18:17,463 --> 00:18:18,797
Yes, I love it.

480
00:18:18,864 --> 00:18:22,000
-How long does this last?
-Two meals.

481
00:18:22,067 --> 00:18:24,136
-That's a lot.
-Do you cook it in a huge cauldron?

482
00:18:24,203 --> 00:18:28,073
That's a whole rice paddy's worth
of freshwater snails.

