1201
00:46:51,742 --> 00:46:53,577
-to record this conversation.
-Is that so?

1202
00:46:53,644 --> 00:46:55,412
Chef Eun-yeong mumbled to herself,

1203
00:46:55,479 --> 00:46:58,115
"I won against all of them,

1204
00:46:58,182 --> 00:47:00,384
so I can win against Hyun-suk too."

1205
00:47:00,450 --> 00:47:02,052
THE MOTH TO A FLAME BLABS(?)

1206
00:47:02,119 --> 00:47:04,521
I started in fourth place,

1207
00:47:04,588 --> 00:47:08,091
so I thought it would be impossible
for me to reach the final round.

1208
00:47:08,959 --> 00:47:10,994
But after beating them one after another,

1209
00:47:11,061 --> 00:47:13,597
I realized that anything was possible,

1210
00:47:13,664 --> 00:47:17,401
that there was no reason
for me to lose against Chef Hyun-suk.

1211
00:47:17,467 --> 00:47:18,402
Love the confidence.

1212
00:47:18,468 --> 00:47:20,804
She's now cooking four times in a row
from the previous episode,

1213
00:47:20,871 --> 00:47:22,573
so it must be physically straining.

1214
00:47:22,639 --> 00:47:24,575
-Four times is rough.
-It must be hard.

1215
00:47:24,641 --> 00:47:25,709
The record shows

1216
00:47:25,776 --> 00:47:27,811
that Hyun-suk won every time
the two fought each other.

1217
00:47:27,878 --> 00:47:30,380
They fought twice, and he won both times.

1218
00:47:30,447 --> 00:47:32,783
-That's the record.
-That could be a problem.

1219
00:47:33,350 --> 00:47:34,751
-Don't be scared.
-You know what?

1220
00:47:34,818 --> 00:47:36,954
He didn't eat anything in the green room.

1221
00:47:37,020 --> 00:47:39,656
-Right. He didn't.
-He hasn't eaten all day.

1222
00:47:39,723 --> 00:47:41,925
Could this mean Hyun-suk is also nervous?

1223
00:47:41,992 --> 00:47:44,228
-Not even a snack?
-He had a single banana earlier,

1224
00:47:44,294 --> 00:47:46,196
and I'm a bit concerned about that.

1225
00:47:46,263 --> 00:47:47,798
What? It's slippery, so he can slip off.

1226
00:47:47,865 --> 00:47:51,735
The two of us cracked an egg
and got cracked by Eun-yeong.

1227
00:47:51,802 --> 00:47:53,170
I had a banana as soon as I got here.

1228
00:47:53,237 --> 00:47:55,405
You had a banana? That was why!

1229
00:47:55,472 --> 00:47:57,808
We either slipped or got cracked.

1230
00:47:57,875 --> 00:47:59,610
I need a setup like this

1231
00:47:59,676 --> 00:48:01,111
for my challenge to be worthy.

1232
00:48:01,178 --> 00:48:02,479
That's what Chef Hyun-suk does.

1233
00:48:02,546 --> 00:48:03,680
I'LL DESTROY THAT CURSE

1234
00:48:03,747 --> 00:48:05,315
-That's why…
-They all slipped and fell.

1235
00:48:05,382 --> 00:48:07,985
I just remembered something
and got chills.

1236
00:48:08,051 --> 00:48:10,220
I had a roll of <i>gimbap</i> this morning.

1237
00:48:10,287 --> 00:48:11,622
You only had <i>gimbap?</i>

1238
00:48:11,688 --> 00:48:13,123
Then he suddenly came

1239
00:48:13,190 --> 00:48:16,493
and asked,
"Chef Eun-yeong, do you want a banana?"

1240
00:48:16,560 --> 00:48:17,761
Wait a minute, everyone.

1241
00:48:17,828 --> 00:48:18,996
It was intentional.

1242
00:48:19,062 --> 00:48:20,797
-He tried to make her eat it.
-It was intentional.

1243
00:48:20,864 --> 00:48:22,900
-It was on purpose!
-But he didn't eat it!

1244
00:48:22,966 --> 00:48:24,268
Do you remember seeing that?

1245
00:48:24,334 --> 00:48:25,669
-I do.
-I saw it too.

1246
00:48:25,736 --> 00:48:27,504
There is no order in the culinary world!

1247
00:48:28,805 --> 00:48:30,240
Look, I ate my banana and thought,

1248
00:48:30,307 --> 00:48:32,342
"A banana might be good for energy."

1249
00:48:33,110 --> 00:48:35,479
"Chef Eun-yeong, do you want a banana?"

1250
00:48:35,913 --> 00:48:37,381
THAT WAS THE TRUTH…

1251
00:48:37,447 --> 00:48:38,715
I didn't offer a poisoned apple like,

1252
00:48:39,716 --> 00:48:41,485
"Chef Eun-yeong, do you want a banana?"

1253
00:48:41,551 --> 00:48:42,886
Look how she distorted the story.

1254
00:48:43,787 --> 00:48:44,855
"Do you want a banana?"

1255
00:48:44,922 --> 00:48:46,223
WHO WILL SLIP FROM THIS ROUND?

1256
00:48:46,290 --> 00:48:48,725
The final match
does not have a specific theme.

1257
00:48:48,792 --> 00:48:50,928
It doesn't matter what you choose to make.

1258
00:48:50,994 --> 00:48:53,497
The result of this round
may cause a transition

1259
00:48:53,563 --> 00:48:57,301
-between generations on the show.
-That could happen.

1260
00:48:57,367 --> 00:48:59,469
-She'll be the female Hyun-suk.
-The era of the young'uns.

1261
00:49:00,404 --> 00:49:04,474
CHEF HYUN-SUK'S INGREDIENTS: ABALONE,
BLUE CRAB, SPINACH, MILK, UNSALTED BUTTER

1262
00:49:04,541 --> 00:49:06,343
My dish is called

1263
00:49:06,910 --> 00:49:08,111
Choi-mpion.

1264
00:49:08,178 --> 00:49:10,113
-Choi-mpion.
-Choi-mpion.

1265
00:49:10,180 --> 00:49:12,115
-I see. Choi, like your last name.
-Choi-mpion.

1266
00:49:12,182 --> 00:49:14,017
-Choi-mpion.
-Choi-mpion.

1267
00:49:14,084 --> 00:49:16,853
As always, I may have to begin

1268
00:49:16,920 --> 00:49:19,389
a fight against myself.

1269
00:49:19,456 --> 00:49:21,291
-What are you making?
-Actually…

1270
00:49:21,858 --> 00:49:24,328
-The last dish of the year.
-…I've always wanted to make this here.

1271
00:49:24,895 --> 00:49:27,130
-I wanted to make a Wellington.
-What?

1272
00:49:27,197 --> 00:49:28,632
-A Wellington?
-Right now?

1273
00:49:28,699 --> 00:49:32,069
<i>It's a pretty quick fix</i>
<i>with some pie dough</i>

1274
00:49:32,135 --> 00:49:34,705
<i>because it can just go into an oven.</i>

1275
00:49:34,771 --> 00:49:36,273
-<i>It'll be amazing if you do it.</i>
-<i>Yes.</i>

1276
00:49:36,340 --> 00:49:38,742
<i>But you could've taken an easier way.</i>

1277
00:49:38,809 --> 00:49:40,978
I didn't think it would be possible,

1278
00:49:41,044 --> 00:49:42,813
but after all, this is the final match,

1279
00:49:42,879 --> 00:49:44,781
so I want to challenge myself.

1280
00:49:44,848 --> 00:49:46,917
Also, Wellingtons
are usually made with steak,

1281
00:49:46,984 --> 00:49:49,486
but I'll use seafood instead

1282
00:49:49,553 --> 00:49:51,355
and make an abalone Wellington.

1283
00:49:51,421 --> 00:49:55,292
-What?
-I'll serve it with some bisque cream…

1284
00:49:55,359 --> 00:49:57,294
-That's impossible.
-…for an undefeatable taste.

1285
00:49:57,361 --> 00:50:00,330
An abalone Wellington
is something that just can't lose.

1286
00:50:00,397 --> 00:50:01,832
-I see.
-My gosh.

1287
00:50:01,898 --> 00:50:04,267
-Can you do that in 15 minutes?
-It sounds risky.

1288
00:50:04,334 --> 00:50:05,736
It is not possible in 15 minutes.

1289
00:50:05,802 --> 00:50:08,005
That is why you are all jealous of me,

1290
00:50:08,071 --> 00:50:10,340
because I, Choi Hyun-suk,
takes up a challenge like that.

1291
00:50:10,407 --> 00:50:12,609
Why do you reckon geniuses are lonely?

1292
00:50:13,610 --> 00:50:15,245
Good luck, Eun-yeong.

1293
00:50:15,312 --> 00:50:16,346
You got this, Eun-yeong!

1294
00:50:16,413 --> 00:50:18,081
-You have to win, Eun-yeong.
-You must.

1295
00:50:18,148 --> 00:50:19,516
I was a huge fan,

1296
00:50:20,917 --> 00:50:22,252
but I'm not sure anymore.

1297
00:50:22,919 --> 00:50:24,221
You're right on.

1298
00:50:24,287 --> 00:50:27,257
The way he speaks
leaves such a bad taste in the mouth.

1299
00:50:27,324 --> 00:50:30,360
-But he always delivers with his dishes.
-That's true.

1300
00:50:31,294 --> 00:50:32,529
CHEF EUN-YEONG'S INGREDIENTS:

1301
00:50:32,596 --> 00:50:35,365
PORK BELLY, CUTLASSFISH, CABBAGE,
PICKLED GREEN PLUM, OYSTER SAUCE

1302
00:50:35,432 --> 00:50:39,269
Up against him is Chef Eun-yeong.
What are you making?

1303
00:50:39,336 --> 00:50:40,637
The dish I'm making is

1304
00:50:40,704 --> 00:50:42,839
Dumplings to Beat Choi Hyun-suk.

1305
00:50:43,507 --> 00:50:45,342
-Dumplings to Beat Choi Hyun-suk.
-Dumplings.

1306
00:50:45,409 --> 00:50:48,111
-Dumplings to beat him.
-She'll beat him with dumplings.

1307
00:50:48,178 --> 00:50:50,347
She's using her best moves.

1308
00:50:50,414 --> 00:50:53,750
Dumplings are very significant to me.

1309
00:50:53,817 --> 00:50:55,152
On <i>Culinary Class Wars,</i>

1310
00:50:55,218 --> 00:50:56,987
I was one of the first Black Spoons

1311
00:50:57,054 --> 00:50:59,723
to make it to the top.

1312
00:50:59,790 --> 00:51:02,225
Back then, I made dumplings
with Dongpo pork,

1313
00:51:02,292 --> 00:51:04,227
<i>and many people enjoyed that.</i>

1314
00:51:04,294 --> 00:51:05,128
Thank you.

1315
00:51:05,195 --> 00:51:10,367
<i>My year was very busy</i>
<i>thanks to that dumpling dish.</i>

1316
00:51:10,434 --> 00:51:15,405
So I want to make dumplings again
as I wrap up 2025.

1317
00:51:15,472 --> 00:51:16,706
-She's serious.
-That's nice.

1318
00:51:16,773 --> 00:51:18,942
You just said you made it to the top,
but you meant "survived," right?

1319
00:51:19,009 --> 00:51:21,244
Yes, I meant that I moved up.

1320
00:51:21,311 --> 00:51:23,113
The winner was Chef Sung-jun.

1321
00:51:23,180 --> 00:51:24,648
Yes, right! You won!

1322
00:51:25,048 --> 00:51:26,349
THE WINNER IS HERE

1323
00:51:26,416 --> 00:51:28,518
-She wants to win this.
-That's all she's thinking about.

1324
00:51:28,585 --> 00:51:30,787
-This is the only thing on her mind.
-Yes.

1325
00:51:30,854 --> 00:51:32,989
I understand why.

1326
00:51:33,056 --> 00:51:34,291
I'll make the dumplings

1327
00:51:34,357 --> 00:51:36,927
with pork and cabbage as the foundation,

1328
00:51:36,993 --> 00:51:39,062
and I'll add some grilled cutlassfish.

1329
00:51:39,129 --> 00:51:40,097
-My gosh.
-Fish dumplings?

1330
00:51:40,163 --> 00:51:42,899
-You'll be able to taste many flavors.
-Cutlassfish dumplings?

1331
00:51:42,966 --> 00:51:45,735
-That's a unique mix.
-Pork and cutlassfish.

1332
00:51:45,802 --> 00:51:50,040
And now, let us begin the final match

1333
00:51:50,107 --> 00:51:53,543
that will decide the winner
of this trophy.

1334
00:51:53,610 --> 00:51:55,345
-My gosh.
-It's the last match of the year.

1335
00:51:55,412 --> 00:51:56,413
It's the end.

1336
00:51:56,480 --> 00:51:58,782
Let us begin

1337
00:51:58,849 --> 00:52:02,052
the 2025 <i>Chef & My Fridge</i> Championship,

1338
00:52:02,119 --> 00:52:04,087
the final match.

1339
00:52:04,154 --> 00:52:07,357
Their aprons are in black and white too.

1340
00:52:07,424 --> 00:52:08,992
-You're right.
-Yes.

1341
00:52:09,059 --> 00:52:11,695
-The Black Spoon and the White Spoon.
-Yes.

1342
00:52:12,262 --> 00:52:16,233
This man will show the class
as the oldest member of the show.

1343
00:52:16,299 --> 00:52:19,736
Chef Choi Hyun-suk,
the first place of the regular season.

1344
00:52:19,803 --> 00:52:22,439
This woman will prove
that the generations have shifted.

1345
00:52:22,506 --> 00:52:27,043
The unrelenting phoenix,
Chef Park Eun-yeong.

1346
00:52:27,110 --> 00:52:28,945
Which one of them

1347
00:52:29,012 --> 00:52:32,649
will take the trophy
for the 2025 Championship?

1348
00:52:32,716 --> 00:52:36,386
Let the 15-minute cook-off
for the final match begin!

1349
00:52:37,154 --> 00:52:39,456
-You can do this!
-The final round begins!

1350
00:52:39,523 --> 00:52:41,291
It's the final round!

1351
00:52:41,725 --> 00:52:44,094
THE LAST MATCH OF 2025

1352
00:52:44,294 --> 00:52:45,996
CHEERING MORE PASSIONATELY THAN EVER

1353
00:52:46,062 --> 00:52:47,797
I hope they both make this
an awesome match.

1354
00:52:47,864 --> 00:52:51,568
Chef Jong-won will accompany Jung-hwan
for the last five-minute check.

1355
00:52:51,635 --> 00:52:54,104
Hyun-suk is trying to make a Wellington.

1356
00:52:54,171 --> 00:52:55,839
-He's getting blue crab meat.
-Blue crabs?

1357
00:52:56,540 --> 00:52:57,874
-For the bisque.
-With blue crabs?

1358
00:52:57,941 --> 00:53:00,310
He made bisque once before,

1359
00:53:00,377 --> 00:53:03,213
but it didn't turn out as nicely
as he expected, so he's improving on it.

1360
00:53:03,280 --> 00:53:05,448
-He wants to make a perfect bisque.
-He's roasting those?

1361
00:53:05,515 --> 00:53:08,418
If he wins today,
he can make up for that slump.

1362
00:53:08,485 --> 00:53:10,387
Isn't it tough to make
a Wellington in 15 minutes?

1363
00:53:10,453 --> 00:53:11,922
-Right?
-It's not easy, right?

1364
00:53:11,988 --> 00:53:14,057
It'll depend on what he uses
as the pie crust.

1365
00:53:14,124 --> 00:53:16,326
-Does she have pie dough?
-She doesn't.

1366
00:53:16,393 --> 00:53:18,762
-I don't see it.
-He only has flour to work with.

1367
00:53:18,828 --> 00:53:21,431
-It may be crêpe batter.
-He parboils the spinach.

1368
00:53:21,498 --> 00:53:23,934
-And abalones.
-Look at him go.

1369
00:53:24,000 --> 00:53:27,437
Many experts expect Hyun-suk to win.

1370
00:53:28,538 --> 00:53:31,208
Eun-yeong's eyes are burning.

1371
00:53:31,274 --> 00:53:33,310
So you'll grill the cutlassfish first

1372
00:53:33,376 --> 00:53:34,511
-to use as a filling?
-Yes.

1373
00:53:34,578 --> 00:53:36,846
On the other side,
Eun-yeong is making dumplings.

1374
00:53:36,913 --> 00:53:37,814
CABBAGE FOR DUMPLINGS

1375
00:53:37,881 --> 00:53:38,949
SALT

1376
00:53:39,015 --> 00:53:40,884
SALTING THE CHOPPED NAPA CABBAGE

1377
00:53:40,951 --> 00:53:43,486
Chef Eun-yeong is also grinding meat.

1378
00:53:44,154 --> 00:53:46,189
-Is it pork?
-It's pork.

1379
00:53:46,256 --> 00:53:48,225
Stay calm.

1380
00:53:48,291 --> 00:53:50,994
Adding water to meat
will make it more tender.

1381
00:53:51,061 --> 00:53:54,197
There are many spectators
who are here to root for Eun-yeong.

1382
00:53:54,264 --> 00:53:59,069
But Hyun-suk will probably be the champion
unless he makes a dire mistake.

1383
00:53:59,135 --> 00:54:00,503
-He cooks the crab meat first.
-Yes.

1384
00:54:00,937 --> 00:54:01,938
TO MY CONCERTO OF A RECIPE

1385
00:54:02,439 --> 00:54:04,808
THIS IS THE FINALE

1386
00:54:05,375 --> 00:54:07,177
THE AUDIENCE GOES WILD

1387
00:54:07,244 --> 00:54:08,311
That was so cool.

1388
00:54:08,378 --> 00:54:10,480
-He was like a conductor.
-Right?

1389
00:54:10,547 --> 00:54:12,115
Although his shoulders
can't go up as high.

1390
00:54:13,516 --> 00:54:14,851
-He has frozen shoulders.
-Frozen shoulders?

1391
00:54:14,918 --> 00:54:16,686
And he's not wearing his glasses.

1392
00:54:16,753 --> 00:54:18,989
-So his aim isn't accurate.
-No.

1393
00:54:19,189 --> 00:54:20,790
FRIED CRAB MEAT AND INNARDS, OUT

1394
00:54:20,857 --> 00:54:23,693
Chef Eun-yeong is kneading the dough
for the dumpling skin.

1395
00:54:23,760 --> 00:54:25,328
She's kneading with hot water.

1396
00:54:25,595 --> 00:54:26,529
HOT WATER

1397
00:54:26,596 --> 00:54:30,333
Chef Eun-yeong makes dumpling skin!

1398
00:54:30,400 --> 00:54:34,571
-It's not easy to make it from scratch.
-No.

1399
00:54:34,638 --> 00:54:37,007
-She must be exhausted too.
-Yes.

1400
00:54:37,073 --> 00:54:38,174
Show the power of the young'uns.

1401
00:54:38,241 --> 00:54:40,710
I want to give her a hand
in kneading the dough.

1402
00:54:41,177 --> 00:54:42,245
CHEF HYUN-SUK MAKES HIS DOUGH TOO

1403
00:54:42,312 --> 00:54:45,015
-The dough.
-What dough? Wait, right.

1404
00:54:45,081 --> 00:54:46,283
He's making pastry.

1405
00:54:46,349 --> 00:54:47,651
-Pastry dough?
-Is he mixing it?

1406
00:54:47,717 --> 00:54:50,020
-And eggs.
-That's a huge bowl.

1407
00:54:50,086 --> 00:54:52,022
Chef Hyun-suk checks for time.

1408
00:54:52,088 --> 00:54:54,257
He must be making the dough
for the Wellington.

1409
00:54:54,324 --> 00:54:56,359
Does he have enough time
to knead and cook it?

1410
00:54:56,426 --> 00:54:57,827
MIXING AGAIN

1411
00:54:57,894 --> 00:54:59,562
-Another egg?
-Wait, no!

1412
00:54:59,629 --> 00:55:01,831
-It came off.
-Please watch your hand.

1413
00:55:01,898 --> 00:55:04,067
That could've gone very badly.

1414
00:55:04,134 --> 00:55:05,335
-Right now…
-Stay calm.

1415
00:55:05,402 --> 00:55:08,972
-One mistake will end his recipe for good.
-That's right.

1416
00:55:09,039 --> 00:55:10,774
He keeps checking the time

1417
00:55:10,840 --> 00:55:14,444
because this isn't an easy dish
to make in 15 minutes.

1418
00:55:14,511 --> 00:55:17,347
Even Hyun-suk feels nervous right now.

1419
00:55:17,414 --> 00:55:19,683
It means he's quite anxious.

1420
00:55:19,749 --> 00:55:20,650
That's the dough.

1421
00:55:20,717 --> 00:55:21,651
I'M NOT

1422
00:55:22,218 --> 00:55:23,520
WOW

1423
00:55:23,586 --> 00:55:25,021
That was so cool!

1424
00:55:25,488 --> 00:55:26,856
ANXIETY IS FOR THE WEAK

1425
00:55:26,923 --> 00:55:28,692
-That was cool.
-That was so cool!

1426
00:55:29,292 --> 00:55:30,827
He attacks her with that performance.

1427
00:55:30,894 --> 00:55:32,829
THE FLOUR TERRORIST

1428
00:55:32,896 --> 00:55:33,797
Stay calm, Eun-yeong.

1429
00:55:33,863 --> 00:55:35,632
The dough looks great.

1430
00:55:35,699 --> 00:55:37,867
-Does it? That dough…
-Yes.

1431
00:55:37,934 --> 00:55:41,638
He'll probably wrap abalones with that
and cook everything together.

1432
00:55:41,705 --> 00:55:43,907
They're both using flour,

1433
00:55:43,973 --> 00:55:46,443
and one is Asian, Chinese, to be exact,

1434
00:55:46,509 --> 00:55:48,678
while the other
