-Chef Hyun-suk!

1673
01:04:53,189 --> 01:04:54,457
He's praying!

1674
01:04:54,523 --> 01:04:56,192
-"Please get cooked."
-Come on. You need to pray.

1675
01:04:56,259 --> 01:04:57,293
WHY ARE THESE TWO SO EXCITED?

1676
01:04:57,360 --> 01:04:59,128
Eun-yeong is still busy cooking.

1677
01:04:59,195 --> 01:05:02,665
It looks like she's making soy sauce
for the dumplings.

1678
01:05:02,732 --> 01:05:04,166
Hyun-suk begins to serve the dish.

1679
01:05:04,233 --> 01:05:06,135
He actually made that sauce?

1680
01:05:06,202 --> 01:05:09,071
-It's a piece of art.
-You have about a minute left.

1681
01:05:09,138 --> 01:05:10,506
Fifty seconds.

1682
01:05:10,573 --> 01:05:11,941
Hyun-suk plates the food.

1683
01:05:12,008 --> 01:05:13,910
-Who will finish first?
-He's so composed.

1684
01:05:13,976 --> 01:05:15,578
He's making a pattern.

1685
01:05:15,645 --> 01:05:17,013
-It's so pretty.
-It's beautiful.

1686
01:05:17,079 --> 01:05:18,247
Forty seconds.

1687
01:05:18,314 --> 01:05:20,683
-Forty seconds!
-He's pulling it out of the oven!

1688
01:05:20,750 --> 01:05:21,651
It looks hot!

1689
01:05:21,717 --> 01:05:24,186
-It looks hot!
-Does it look cooked?

1690
01:05:24,954 --> 01:05:26,455
A PERFECTLY WELL-COOKED WELLINGTON

1691
01:05:26,522 --> 01:05:28,724
-Has it been cooked?
-It's been cooked!

1692
01:05:28,791 --> 01:05:30,526
-It's been cooked!
-Really?

1693
01:05:30,593 --> 01:05:32,461
-It's shaped like an abalone.
-No way.

1694
01:05:32,528 --> 01:05:33,629
Thirty seconds!

1695
01:05:33,696 --> 01:05:34,964
-Thirty seconds!
-Thirty seconds!

1696
01:05:35,031 --> 01:05:36,132
That's impressive.

1697
01:05:37,366 --> 01:05:38,901
-Thirty seconds!
-Thirty seconds!

1698
01:05:38,968 --> 01:05:41,304
-He finishes!
-He finishes! Chef Hyun-suk finishes!

1699
01:05:41,370 --> 01:05:42,405
Eun-yeong still needs more time!

1700
01:05:42,471 --> 01:05:46,509
-Eun-yeong, you have enough time.
-You have 20 seconds left!

1701
01:05:46,575 --> 01:05:47,543
Twenty seconds!

1702
01:05:47,610 --> 01:05:49,812
-I hope it's cooked.
-I hope the dumplings are cooked.

1703
01:05:49,879 --> 01:05:51,414
She gets her sauce ready first.

1704
01:05:51,480 --> 01:05:53,049
-She can make use of the time.
-Nine.

1705
01:05:53,115 --> 01:05:55,117
-She has time.
-Eight.

1706
01:05:55,184 --> 01:05:56,152
You got this, Eun-yeong!

1707
01:05:56,218 --> 01:05:58,220
-Five. Four.
-You can do this!

1708
01:05:58,287 --> 01:06:00,523
-Three. Two.
-Beat your Goliath!

1709
01:06:00,589 --> 01:06:02,425
INFLATED HEIGHT AND EGO(?)

1710
01:06:02,925 --> 01:06:05,528
THE FINAL MATCH OF 2025 ENDS

1711
01:06:05,594 --> 01:06:07,096
Time's up!

1712
01:06:07,163 --> 01:06:08,431
THE CRAZIEST FIGHT YET

1713
01:06:08,497 --> 01:06:10,700
-That was insane.
-You've done so well.

1714
01:06:10,766 --> 01:06:12,735
I hope the dumplings are cooked.

1715
01:06:12,802 --> 01:06:13,769
SERVING IT IN THE POT

1716
01:06:13,836 --> 01:06:14,904
Okay.

1717
01:06:14,971 --> 01:06:16,238
-Wait.
-Resting.

1718
01:06:16,305 --> 01:06:17,506
Do you really think

1719
01:06:17,573 --> 01:06:19,842
serving it in the pot
suits the final round?

1720
01:06:19,909 --> 01:06:21,177
It's a new trend.

1721
01:06:21,243 --> 01:06:23,079
It's the new trend in plating!

1722
01:06:23,746 --> 01:06:25,314
SHE SUBMITS HER DISH WITH VIGOR

1723
01:06:25,381 --> 01:06:28,284
-That's her plating technique.
-Yes, serve it in the pot.

1724
01:06:28,851 --> 01:06:29,919
THE FINAL DISHES TAKE OFF

1725
01:06:29,986 --> 01:06:32,388
-Everything is up to pure luck.
-Look at that pot.

1726
01:06:32,455 --> 01:06:34,156
She couldn't check the dumplings.

1727
01:06:34,223 --> 01:06:35,992
THE TWO PUT ON THE BEST COOK-OFF

1728
01:06:36,058 --> 01:06:38,527
Does this mean
the dumplings may be medium-rare?

1729
01:06:38,594 --> 01:06:41,097
Yes, if they didn't cook through yet.

1730
01:06:41,163 --> 01:06:42,999
It's all up to sheer luck.

1731
01:06:43,065 --> 01:06:48,004
The final dishes made for Su-ji
are both done.

1732
01:06:48,070 --> 01:06:53,175
Both dishes seem worthy
of the final match.

1733
01:06:53,242 --> 01:06:54,543
And Chef Eun-yeong

1734
01:06:54,610 --> 01:06:58,214
called that her personal plating technique
and served it like that.

1735
01:06:58,280 --> 01:07:00,082
-She should've served just the top…
-Like a Gen Z girl.

1736
01:07:00,149 --> 01:07:02,752
…but she served the pot underneath too.

1737
01:07:02,818 --> 01:07:04,687
-That's how they do it in Seongsu-dong.
-She's keeping it warm.

1738
01:07:04,754 --> 01:07:05,955
Yes, that's the trend.

1739
01:07:06,022 --> 01:07:07,256
-How trendy.
-All right, then.

1740
01:07:07,323 --> 01:07:09,925
The whole world has its eyes on you two.

1741
01:07:09,992 --> 01:07:14,463
She'll try the dish made by Chef Hyun-suk,
who finished first in the regular league.

1742
01:07:14,530 --> 01:07:17,900
AN ABALONE WELLINGTON
MADE IN JUST 15 MINUTES

1743
01:07:19,702 --> 01:07:22,872
CRAB BISQUE MEETS ABALONE
IN THE TENDER PIE

1744
01:07:23,906 --> 01:07:28,044
CHEF CHOI HYUN-SUK'S CHOI-MPION

1745
01:07:28,110 --> 01:07:29,979
He made a Wellington.

1746
01:07:30,046 --> 01:07:30,946
IMPRESSED

1747
01:07:31,013 --> 01:07:33,916
-I wonder what it's like.
-Right?

1748
01:07:33,983 --> 01:07:35,084
It must taste good.

1749
01:07:36,352 --> 01:07:38,988
-How did he do that in 15 minutes?
-That's…

1750
01:07:40,089 --> 01:07:42,158
It's an abalone Wellington…

1751
01:07:42,224 --> 01:07:45,194
-It's so easy to cut.
-…served with crab bisque.

1752
01:07:45,261 --> 01:07:46,762
It looks so tender.

1753
01:07:46,829 --> 01:07:48,964
-It's so tender.
-I see.

1754
01:07:49,031 --> 01:07:50,866
-I'll cut it once more.
-It's so pretty.

1755
01:07:50,933 --> 01:07:52,101
-I want to see the cut.
-It's cooked well.

1756
01:07:52,168 --> 01:07:53,335
CUTTING CAREFULLY…

1757
01:07:53,402 --> 01:07:55,871
-Shucks, whatever.
-"Shucks, whatever."

1758
01:07:55,938 --> 01:07:57,540
-You should scoop it up.
-Yes.

1759
01:07:57,606 --> 01:07:59,875
-Can we see the cross-section?
-One second.

1760
01:07:59,942 --> 01:08:01,644
Let me take the footage.

1761
01:08:02,578 --> 01:08:03,846
LOOKING DELICIOUS

1762
01:08:03,913 --> 01:08:06,615
The cross-section of the abalone.
It was easy to cut.

1763
01:08:06,682 --> 01:08:07,750
-Yes.
-Yes.

1764
01:08:07,817 --> 01:08:09,351
How do you feel?

1765
01:08:09,418 --> 01:08:12,655
Well, this is a global show,

1766
01:08:12,721 --> 01:08:16,192
so I should review this dish
using my most global persona.

1767
01:08:16,992 --> 01:08:17,927
Currently,

1768
01:08:17,993 --> 01:08:20,529
in Korea, he's known as

1769
01:08:20,596 --> 01:08:22,231
-the "skull chef," I think?
-The head chef.

1770
01:08:22,298 --> 01:08:25,100
He's someone who makes good dishes.

1771
01:08:26,936 --> 01:08:29,538
-All right, then.
-That was excellent.

1772
01:08:29,605 --> 01:08:31,407
It's not wrong, but it sounds lousy.

1773
01:08:31,474 --> 01:08:33,542
-The world has its eyes on you.
-"The skull chef."

1774
01:08:33,609 --> 01:08:36,212
-Should she try it with lots of sauce?
-She should scoop a lot.

1775
01:08:36,278 --> 01:08:38,147
-Get a lot of sauce on it.
-Lots of sauce.

1776
01:08:38,214 --> 01:08:40,182
LOTS OF SAUCE

1777
01:08:40,249 --> 01:08:42,318
I wonder if it's been cooked well.

1778
01:08:42,384 --> 01:08:44,353
-Here I go.
-Let's go!

1779
01:08:45,921 --> 01:08:47,223
That's Chef Hyun-suk's dish.

1780
01:08:47,289 --> 01:08:48,290
YUM

1781
01:08:50,693 --> 01:08:52,261
Fireworks are going off in her mouth.

1782
01:08:53,562 --> 01:08:55,297
SMILING

1783
01:08:57,199 --> 01:08:58,400
Has it been cooked well?

1784
01:08:58,467 --> 01:09:00,970
-She looks moved.
-I wonder if the sauce works well too.

1785
01:09:02,371 --> 01:09:05,808
Su-ji took a look at Chef Hyun-suk.

1786
01:09:06,342 --> 01:09:09,478
I've never had abalone this tender.

1787
01:09:10,813 --> 01:09:12,014
I have never had anything like it.

1788
01:09:12,581 --> 01:09:13,549
A PERSONA CHANGE IN REAL-TIME

1789
01:09:13,616 --> 01:09:14,950
-Has it been cooked?
-Yes.

1790
01:09:15,017 --> 01:09:16,285
Yes?

1791
01:09:16,352 --> 01:09:17,553
What's on the outside?

1792
01:09:18,154 --> 01:09:19,688
Pie crust.

1793
01:09:19,755 --> 01:09:23,759
It's so soft and smooth.
It has zero dryness.

1794
01:09:24,226 --> 01:09:25,861
SHARING THE SMOOTHNESS BY MIMING

1795
01:09:25,928 --> 01:09:26,762
Also,

1796
01:09:26,829 --> 01:09:31,367
I want to mix a bowl of rice
with this sauce right now.

1797
01:09:31,433 --> 01:09:33,702
-The sauce?
-It's so good.

1798
01:09:33,769 --> 01:09:35,871
-The bisque sauce.
-It's a guaranteed win.

1799
01:09:36,472 --> 01:09:39,975
Wait, did you use the crab meat
for this sauce?

1800
01:09:40,042 --> 01:09:41,510
<i>I stir-fried the crab meat</i>

1801
01:09:41,577 --> 01:09:42,912
<i>and used it as the Wellington filling.</i>

1802
01:09:42,978 --> 01:09:46,148
<i>Then I roasted the shell in the oven</i>
<i>to make that sauce.</i>

1803
01:09:46,215 --> 01:09:50,719
I can smell and taste the crab
even in the sauce.

1804
01:09:50,786 --> 01:09:52,755
-I see.
-On top of that, it's creamy,

1805
01:09:52,821 --> 01:09:55,891
so it's almost like soup.

1806
01:09:55,958 --> 01:09:57,393
I love it.

1807
01:09:57,960 --> 01:10:00,029
Yes, it's just my style!

1808
01:10:02,097 --> 01:10:04,166
-It's just Su-ji's style.
-Yes.

1809
01:10:04,233 --> 01:10:05,968
This is so precious. It's like a treasure.

1810
01:10:06,035 --> 01:10:09,238
It's like treasure?
She must want to save it.

1811
01:10:09,305 --> 01:10:10,139
Have another bite, then.

1812
01:10:10,206 --> 01:10:11,607
-May I?
-Another piece.

1813
01:10:13,275 --> 01:10:14,843
-What was that?
-Because that kid

1814
01:10:14,910 --> 01:10:17,546
-told me to leave him some.
-"That kid"?

1815
01:10:17,613 --> 01:10:19,281
I'm dying to try it.

1816
01:10:19,348 --> 01:10:22,318
-When will I get to try his food?
-I know.

1817
01:10:22,384 --> 01:10:24,253
-Go to his restaurant.
-If this is…

1818
01:10:24,553 --> 01:10:26,522
YOU CAN GO TO HIS RESTAURANT

1819
01:10:27,089 --> 01:10:28,591
I need lots of sauce.

1820
01:10:28,657 --> 01:10:31,460
ANOTHER BITE WITH LOTS OF SAUCE

1821
01:10:31,527 --> 01:10:33,963
-It looks good.
-She eats it so well.

1822
01:10:34,029 --> 01:10:35,764
MMM

1823
01:10:35,831 --> 01:10:37,099
It makes her tilt her head.

1824
01:10:37,666 --> 01:10:39,702
I'M DYING TO FIND OUT!

1825
01:10:39,768 --> 01:10:43,405
This is why everyone says
Choi Hyun-suk is the best.

1826
01:10:44,373 --> 01:10:47,243
You just tried a dish
made by the first place of the show.

1827
01:10:47,309 --> 01:10:49,345
Next, Chef Eun-yeong's dish.

1828
01:10:49,845 --> 01:10:51,714
A PERSONAL CREATION OF DUMPLINGS
TO BEAT CHOI HYUN-SUK

1829
01:10:52,448 --> 01:10:55,417
A NEW MIX BETWEEN PORK AND CUTLASSFISH

1830
01:10:56,085 --> 01:10:58,354
SERVED WITH GREEN PLUM PICKLES
IN SOY SAUCE

1831
01:10:59,488 --> 01:11:02,658
CHEF PARK EUN-YEONG'S
DUMPLINGS TO BEAT CHOI HYUN-SUK

1832
01:11:02,725 --> 01:11:05,361
She served it with the pot at the bottom.

1833
01:11:05,928 --> 01:11:07,496
-Do I open it?
-Are the dumplings cooked?

1834
01:11:07,896 --> 01:11:09,164
OPEN IT!

1835
01:11:09,231 --> 01:11:11,867
-By now, yes.
-It rested there for ten minutes.

1836
01:11:11,934 --> 01:11:15,037
-The dumplings.
-Look at the steam.

1837
01:11:15,104 --> 01:11:17,273
-It has to be cooked.
-It's still steamy.

1838
01:11:17,339 --> 01:11:18,741
It looks steamy.

1839
01:11:18,807 --> 01:11:20,075
BUT WITH THE STEAMER IN FRONT…

1840
01:11:20,142 --> 01:11:21,577
I feel like I've become

1841
01:11:21,644 --> 01:11:23,078
Sammo Hung in one of his films.

1842
01:11:24,313 --> 01:11:27,850
-Then should I review this as him?
-Sure, like a Hong Konger.

1843
01:11:27,916 --> 01:11:29,918
-Should I open it?
-The Hong Kong style.

1844
01:11:29,985 --> 01:11:31,253
Now, the dumplings.

1845
01:11:31,320 --> 01:11:32,154
HONG KONG STYLE?

1846
01:11:34,523 --> 01:11:35,391
Play the background music.

1847
01:11:35,991 --> 01:11:38,227
GOODNESS GRACIOUS, THESE DUMPLINGS…

1848
01:11:38,894 --> 01:11:40,963
EXCELLENT

1849
01:11:41,030 --> 01:11:42,798
-She's so crazy.
-All right.

1850
01:11:42,865 --> 01:11:45,000
Hyun-suk has made a French dish,

1851
01:11:45,067 --> 01:11:46,669
and this one is Chinese.

1852
01:11:46,735 --> 01:11:47,569
That looks…

1853
01:11:48,871 --> 01:11:51,206
-She made it look so pretty.
-It must be so juicy.

1854
01:11:51,273 --> 01:11:52,641
Eun-yeong's dumplings are so good.

1855
01:11:54,143 --> 01:11:55,377
THE JUICE DRIPS

1856
01:11:55,444 --> 01:11:57,246
-It must be so hot!
-Oh, no.

1857
01:11:57,313 --> 01:11:58,280
Look how juicy that is.

1858
01:11:58,347 --> 01:11:59,448
Was that her drooling?

1859
01:11:59,515 --> 01:12:02,418
No, I wasn't drooling.

1860
01:12:02,484 --> 01:12:04,019
-Was she drooling?
-Did she drool?

1861
01:12:04,086 --> 01:12:05,888
STOPS ANY SUSPICIONS OF DROOLING
WITH HER EYEBROWS

1862
01:12:05,954 --> 01:12:07,623
-It must be so hot.
-It was the juice.

1863
01:12:09,458 --> 01:12:10,926
Man, that was hot.

1864
01:12:11,493 --> 01:12:12,895
SIDE EFFECT OF THE TRENDY PLATING STYLE

1865
01:12:13,462 --> 01:12:14,997
RETRYING AFTER THE DROOLING SCANDAL

1866
01:12:15,064 --> 01:12:16,532
Watch your lips.

1867
01:12:17,733 --> 01:12:18,701
SLURP

1868
01:12:18,767 --> 01:12:19,768
Let me leave this here.

1869
01:12:22,338 --> 01:12:23,939
EVEN THE JUICE ON THE SPOON

1870
01:12:24,006 --> 01:12:26,108
-My gosh.
-That soup.

1871
01:12:26,175 --> 01:12:27,109
The soup.

1872
01:12:28,310 --> 01:12:30,245
SALIVATING

1873
01:12:32,281 --> 01:12:34,750
She used ground pork belly

1874
01:12:34,817 --> 01:12:36,618
-as well as cutlassfish.
-Yes.

1875
01:12:37,953 --> 01:12:39,988
-Did you find fish bones?
-No.

1876
01:12:40,055 --> 01:12:42,858
-No, not fish bones, but the fish.
-It's the fish.

1877
01:12:42,925 --> 01:12:44,093
I thought it had fish bones.

1878
01:12:44,159 --> 01:12:45,728
Can you taste the cutlassfish?

1879
01:12:46,295 --> 01:12:47,896
IT'S SO GOOD

1880
01:12:47,963 --> 01:12:51,467
-Did your heart drop?
-Yes, I thought she found a bone.

1881
01:12:52,034 --> 01:12:53,135
Top it with the pickle.

1882
01:12:53,202 --> 01:12:54,203
Pickled green plum.

1883
01:12:54,269 --> 01:12:55,571
That's the cherry on top.

1884
01:12:55,637 --> 01:12:57,239
Yes, soaked in soy sauce.

1885
01:12:57,306 --> 01:12:59,742
-That's the way to eat it.
-It looked pretty old,

1886
01:12:59,808 --> 01:13:00,876
so we were a bit worried.

1887
01:13:00,943 --> 01:13:02,478
Thank you so much, Eun-yeong.

1888
01:13:03,645 --> 01:13:08,150
It tastes like my grandma's dumplings,
the ones I had before I came here.

1889
01:13:08,384 --> 01:13:09,385
IN ANOTHER PERSONA, LIN ZHAOMING

1890
01:13:09,451 --> 01:13:12,321
And because she added cutlassfish,

1891
01:13:12,388 --> 01:13:15,290
it tasted like
it was made in front of the sea.

1892
01:13:15,657 --> 01:13:17,326
WAS THAT SEA A PART
OF THE YANBIAN PROVINCE?

1893
01:13:17,393 --> 01:13:20,796
I can't believe cutlassfish makes
such a delicious dumpling filling.

1894
01:13:20,863 --> 01:13:23,165
My gosh. I can't believe it.

1895
01:13:23,232 --> 01:13:24,867
You scored a win today, kid.

1896
01:13:25,134 --> 01:13:27,169
YOU SCORED A WIN, EUN-YEONG

1897
01:13:27,236 --> 01:13:28,537
Where are you from?

1898
01:13:28,604 --> 01:13:30,038
-She's so good.
-I'm from Seoul.

1899
01:13:30,272 --> 01:13:32,341
SUDDENLY BECOMES GIRLIE GIRL DDU-JI

1900
01:13:32,908 --> 01:13:33,876
All right.

1901
01:13:33,942 --> 01:13:35,344
DIPS ANOTHER ONE IN THE SAUCE

1902
01:13:35,411 --> 01:13:37,379
She's so good at what she does.

1903
01:13:37,880 --> 01:13:38,847
Goodness, the juice.

1904
01:13:38,914 --> 01:13:40,349
SLURRRRP

1905
01:13:40,416 --> 01:13:42,684
SHE'S SUDDENLY FIGHTING THE DUMPLING

1906
01:13:43,786 --> 01:13:45,521
SHE ALMOST FELL OVER BECAUSE OF THE SOUP

1907
01:13:45,587 --> 01:13:48,090
-She's falling over. I should hold this.
-She couldn't waste it.

1908
01:13:48,157 --> 01:13:50,426
She would've continued to eat it
even as she fell over.

1909
01:13:50,492 --> 01:13:52,127
That looks so good.

1910
01:13:52,194 --> 01:13:53,028
Man.

1911
01:13:54,863 --> 01:13:57,032
WERE THESE DUMPLINGS
TRULY ENOUGH TO BEAT HYUN-SUK?

1912
01:13:57,099 --> 01:14:00,669
I didn't know if I would like
cutlassfish in the dumplings,

1913
01:14:00,736 --> 01:14:03,772
-thinking it could taste a bit too fishy.
-Yes.

1914
01:14:03,839 --> 01:14:05,107
But not at all.

1915
01:14:06,008 --> 01:14:09,077
It felt like the first time
I had eaten a dumpling like this.

1916
01:14:09,144 --> 01:14:11,346
The juice and the cutlassfish
all go so well together.

1917
01:14:11,680 --> 01:14:14,383
REMEMBERING THE DELICIOUSNESS!
GOSH, I WANT SOME AGAIN

1918
01:14:14,450 --> 01:14:18,220
The dumpling skin
is also really thin and nice.

1919
01:14:18,287 --> 01:14:22,024
It's so good. Thank you so much.

1920
01:14:22,090 --> 01:14:24,560
How many times has her persona changed?

1921
01:14:24,626 --> 01:14:27,262
-She was Su-ji just now.
-She has like 20 personalities.

1922
01:14:27,329 --> 01:14:30,666
-She returned to Su-ji at the end.
-Thank you.

1923
01:14:30,732 --> 01:14:33,869
It's now Won-hun's turn.

1924
01:14:33,936 --> 01:14:36,104
-May I try some?
-Yes.

1925
01:14:36,171 --> 01:14:39,141
-Take it. He can't make another one.
-I left half for you.

1926
01:14:39,208 --> 01:14:40,876
Try the piece with the abalone.

1927
01:14:40,943 --> 01:14:42,344
Try it and leave no regrets.

1928
01:14:42,911 --> 01:14:45,080
-Put everything in at once with the sauce.
-It's so tender.

1929
01:14:45,647 --> 01:14:47,816
EVERYTHING IN A BITE!

1930
01:14:50,419 --> 01:14:52,988
The crust's texture
and the sauce's flavor are all important.

1931
01:14:54,156 --> 01:14:55,057
Won-hun?

1932
01:14:55,123 --> 01:14:55,958
GOODNESS

1933
01:14:56,024 --> 01:14:57,526
YOU FELT IT TOO

1934
01:14:57,593 --> 01:14:59,361
-So?
-How did he create this flavor?

1935
01:14:59,428 --> 01:15:01,063
The crust on the outside

1936
01:15:01,129 --> 01:15:05,167
feels like a really soft macaron cookie,

1937
01:15:05,234 --> 01:15:08,270
<i>filled with tender abalone,</i>
<i>and served with delicious sauce.</i>

1938
01:15:08,337 --> 01:15:09,505
When the three came together,

1939
01:15:09,571 --> 01:15:12,474
I realized why he is
the best chef in the world.

1940
01:15:12,541 --> 01:15:15,677
He's not the best in the world, though.
The best of <i>Chef & My Fridge.</i>

1941
01:15:15,744 --> 01:15:18,947
I realized why he is
the best chef of <i>Chef & My Fridge.</i>

1942
01:15:19,014 --> 01:15:20,983
He could be the world's best.
People around the world watch us.

1943
01:15:21,049 --> 01:15:24,553
Next, try Chef Eun-yeong's dumpling.

1944
01:15:25,354 --> 01:15:27,322
The juice is probably exploding
in his mouth.

1945
01:15:27,623 --> 01:15:28,690
DID THE JUICE NOT EXPLODE?

1946
01:15:28,757 --> 01:15:31,260
My gosh. There it is.

1947
01:15:31,326 --> 01:15:32,661
THERE WE GO

1948
01:15:32,728 --> 01:15:34,029
It must be good.

1949
01:15:34,096 --> 01:15:35,664
-I wonder what it's like.
-I think

1950
01:15:35,731 --> 01:15:37,499
my palate works really well

1951
01:15:37,566 --> 01:15:40,769
with whatever Chef Eun-yeong makes.

1952
01:15:40,836 --> 01:15:42,371
<i>Right. He tried all four.</i>

1953
01:15:42,437 --> 01:15:43,839
<i>-Do you like this too?</i>
<i>-It's the fourth time.</i>

1954
01:15:43,906 --> 01:15:45,774
<i>-You had it all four times.</i>
<i>-He did.</i>

1955
01:15:45,841 --> 01:15:50,112
The flavor of the cutlassfish
cuts in here and there as I chew,

1956
01:15:50,178 --> 01:15:51,013
and that's such a kick.

1957
01:15:51,079 --> 01:15:53,382
-So it does play a role.
-It's really good.

1958
01:15:53,448 --> 01:15:56,752
I don't think
I'll get to eat anything like this again.

1959
01:15:57,319 --> 01:15:58,186
A HIGH COMPLIMENT

1960
01:15:58,253 --> 01:15:59,321
We're sorry you only had one.

1961
01:15:59,388 --> 01:16:02,758
Both dishes were worthy
of the final match.

1962
01:16:03,158 --> 01:16:04,326
A TRULY TIGHT MATCH

1963
01:16:04,393 --> 01:16:05,561
<i>It's truly a match of two titans.</i>

1964
01:16:05,627 --> 01:16:06,828
The decision

1965
01:16:06,895 --> 01:16:11,300
is solely made
based on whatever Su-ji chooses.

1966
01:16:11,366 --> 01:16:14,970
<i>Press one to choose the challenger,</i>
<i>Chef Park Eun-yeong.</i>

1967
01:16:15,037 --> 01:16:19,174
<i>Press two to choose Choi Hyun-suk,</i>
<i>who finished first in the regular league.</i>

1968
01:16:19,241 --> 01:16:21,743
Who is worthy of the trophy?
Please make your decision

1969
01:16:21,810 --> 01:16:23,979
and press the button!

1970
01:16:26,882 --> 01:16:27,950
How do you pick just one?

1971
01:16:28,016 --> 01:16:31,186
The dishes were so different.

1972
01:16:31,253 --> 01:16:33,989
The champion will be decided
after she presses the button.

1973
01:16:34,056 --> 01:16:35,157
-That's right.
-Yes.

1974
01:16:35,223 --> 01:16:36,792
-Did you push it?
-Yes.

1975
01:16:36,858 --> 01:16:38,160
-You did?
-I did!

1976
01:16:38,226 --> 01:16:39,227
She pushed the button.

1977
01:16:39,294 --> 01:16:42,230
Who will take the glorious title

1978
01:16:42,297 --> 01:16:46,568
<i>of the best chef of </i>Chef & My Fridge
<i>this year?</i>

1979
01:16:46,635 --> 01:16:50,706
Let us find out Su-ji's decision,
the champion entertainer of 2025.

1980
01:16:50,772 --> 01:16:55,277
Who will become the best chef of 2025,
of the 2025 <i>Chef & My Fridge</i> championship?

1981
01:16:55,344 --> 01:16:56,411
Show us!

1982
01:16:57,646 --> 01:16:59,114
Who will it be?

1983
01:16:59,181 --> 01:17:02,217
-As we wrap up the year…
-I can't watch this.

1984
01:17:02,284 --> 01:17:04,620
…who's going to finish this race
as the best chef?

1985
01:17:04,686 --> 01:17:07,089
The decision was made by Su-ji,
the champion entertainer.

1986
01:17:07,155 --> 01:17:10,125
Will it be Hyun-suk,
who ended first in the regular league?

1987
01:17:10,192 --> 01:17:14,696
Or will it be Eun-yeong,
who rose in a sweeping upturn?

1988
01:17:14,763 --> 01:17:16,632
Who's the champion?

1989
01:17:16,698 --> 01:17:20,369
The champion of the 2025 <i>Chef & My Fridge!</i>

1990
01:17:20,435 --> 01:17:21,670
My head hurts.

1991
01:17:21,737 --> 01:17:23,205
Who is it?

1992
01:17:23,271 --> 01:17:25,340
Who's the best chef?

1993
01:17:25,407 --> 01:17:28,644
-Who's the <i>Chef & My Fridge</i> champion?
-Who is it?

1994
01:17:28,710 --> 01:17:30,512
Who is it?

1995
01:17:35,417 --> 01:17:36,618
Who is it?

1996
01:17:36,685 --> 01:17:39,721
CHOI HYUN-SUK WINS

1997
01:17:39,788 --> 01:17:40,956
Choi Hyun-suk!

1998
01:17:41,023 --> 01:17:43,358
CHEF CHOI HYUN-SUK'S CHOI-MPION WINS

1999
01:17:43,425 --> 01:17:45,227
Choi Hyun-suk wins!

2000
01:17:45,293 --> 01:17:47,362
WATCH ME, I'M THE CHAMPION!

2001
01:17:47,429 --> 01:17:51,266
Choi Hyun-suk is the champion
of the year 2025!

2002
01:17:51,333 --> 01:17:53,101
Good game, Chef Hyun-suk.

2003
01:17:54,336 --> 01:17:56,304
EUN-YEONG ENDS IN 2ND PLACE

2004
01:17:56,371 --> 01:17:58,807
-It must've been so hard to choose.
-You've done well.

2005
01:17:58,874 --> 01:18:02,177
Hyun-suk has been chosen
as the final champion

2006
01:18:02,244 --> 01:18:04,680
of <i>Chef & My Fridge.</i>

2007
01:18:04,746 --> 01:18:06,982
That's my master.

2008
01:18:07,049 --> 01:18:09,818
To be honest, Chef Hyun-suk…

2009
01:18:09,885 --> 01:18:10,852
LOOK AT HIM

2010
01:18:10,919 --> 01:18:12,921
-Please look at him.
-Sure.

2011
01:18:12,988 --> 01:18:15,524
The way he performed and spoke

2012
01:18:15,590 --> 01:18:17,726
made me determined
to choose Chef Eun-yeong

2013
01:18:17,793 --> 01:18:19,961
while they were in the process.

2014
01:18:20,028 --> 01:18:24,633
-But my tongue already said he won.
-You couldn't lie.

2015
01:18:24,700 --> 01:18:26,568
It was absolutely delicious,

2016
01:18:26,635 --> 01:18:28,804
but of course,
the dumplings were great too.

2017
01:18:28,870 --> 01:18:30,739
I could see why you all were the best.

2018
01:18:30,806 --> 01:18:35,577
The fact that I got to compete
against Chef Hyun-suk in the finals

2019
01:18:35,644 --> 01:18:38,080
already made me pleased.

2020
01:18:38,146 --> 01:18:39,548
Do you have any regrets?

2021
01:18:39,614 --> 01:18:42,484
-No, I did my best today.
-I see.

2022
01:18:42,884 --> 01:18:44,853
YOU'RE AMAZING

2023
01:18:44,920 --> 01:18:46,988
She cooked four times today.

2024
01:18:47,055 --> 01:18:49,891
He becomes the final champion of the year

2025
01:18:49,958 --> 01:18:51,827
with 15 stars in the regular season.

2026
01:18:51,893 --> 01:18:52,761
THAT'S ME

2027
01:18:52,828 --> 01:18:56,431
Let's hear a speech
from Chef Choi Hyun-suk.

2028
01:18:56,498 --> 01:19:00,035
I will continue to cook as a chef
who continuously challenges himself.

2029
01:19:00,102 --> 01:19:02,404
Also, the way Chef Eun-yeong

2030
01:19:02,471 --> 01:19:05,640
continuously made her way up
seemed so awesome.

2031
01:19:05,707 --> 01:19:08,076
She's been getting ready
to open her own restaurant,

2032
01:19:08,143 --> 01:19:11,813
and I'd love to make a visit
when she does.

2033
01:19:11,880 --> 01:19:13,215
-Great game.
-Great game.

2034
01:19:13,281 --> 01:19:14,549
GREAT JOB, BOTH OF YOU

2035
01:19:14,950 --> 01:19:16,651
A HEARTWARMING MOMENT TO WRAP UP THE YEAR

2036
01:19:16,718 --> 01:19:19,488
Who do you wish
to share the honor of your victory with?

2037
01:19:19,554 --> 01:19:22,724
The glory of my victory and that trophy

2038
01:19:22,791 --> 01:19:24,359
will remain my personal achievement.

2039
01:19:24,926 --> 01:19:28,263
THE PERSON WHO EVEN LOST HER CATCHPHRASE

2040
01:19:28,530 --> 01:19:30,332
THAT'S AWESOME, MASTER(?)

2041
01:19:30,398 --> 01:19:33,702
Yes, that's what makes him Choi Hyun-suk.

2042
01:19:34,202 --> 01:19:36,605
Su-ji, please deliver

2043
01:19:36,671 --> 01:19:41,076
the trophy to the winner
of the 2025 <i>Chef & My Fridge</i> Championship,

2044
01:19:41,143 --> 01:19:43,011
-Chef Choi Hyun-suk!
-Thank you, it was so delicious.

2045
01:19:43,078 --> 01:19:44,479
CHEF & MY FRIDGE WILL CONTINUE ON IN 2026

2046
01:19:45,147 --> 01:19:47,382
He's the champion of 2025!

2047
01:19:47,449 --> 01:19:49,050
Chef Choi Hyun-suk!

2048
01:19:49,117 --> 01:19:50,118
TA-DA

2049
01:19:50,185 --> 01:19:52,287
STAY TUNED FOR NEXT WEEK'S FRIDGE OWNERS,
RHEE MIN-JUNG AND YOO JI-TAE

2050
01:19:52,354 --> 01:19:53,722
Congratulations.

2051
01:19:54,723 --> 01:19:56,258
<i>Culinary Class Wars Season 2</i> is out,

2052
01:19:56,324 --> 01:19:57,726
and I couldn't lose my fans.

2053
01:19:57,793 --> 01:19:59,294
It's a turf war.

2054
01:19:59,361 --> 01:20:02,397
No one wanted to see me dance
on that show.

2055
01:20:02,964 --> 01:20:04,299
We're here today with amazing guests

2056
01:20:04,366 --> 01:20:05,834
as we start the new year, year 2026.

2057
01:20:05,901 --> 01:20:07,669
I often saw you in quarrels.

2058
01:20:07,736 --> 01:20:09,371
THE CRAZIEST CULINARY WAR BEGINS

2059
01:20:09,437 --> 01:20:10,338
MENACING SOUND EFFECTS

2060
01:20:10,405 --> 01:20:11,273
He's so scary.

2061
01:20:11,339 --> 01:20:12,741
Can you stop me?

2062
01:20:12,808 --> 01:20:14,242
FLUSTERED LAUGHTER

2063
01:20:14,309 --> 01:20:15,877
<i>This is the first round of 2026.</i>

2064
01:20:15,944 --> 01:20:17,746
<i>He's not the old Chef Sam Kim.</i>

2065
01:20:17,813 --> 01:20:18,747
A FACE-OFF OF TWO WHITE SPOONS

2066
01:20:18,814 --> 01:20:20,582
-Is that pasta?
-Isn't that <i>yakisoba?</i>

2067
01:20:20,649 --> 01:20:21,483
It's more like udon.

2068
01:20:21,550 --> 01:20:22,751
It's pasta.

2069
01:20:22,818 --> 01:20:24,119
WAIT, THIS IS CHEF & MY FRIDGE

2070
01:20:25,654 --> 01:20:26,521
HIS SUPPRESSED INSTINCT TO DANCE

2071
01:20:26,788 --> 01:20:29,291
I'M THE FOUNDATION OF CHEF & MY FRIDGE!

2072
01:20:29,357 --> 01:20:31,526
It looks like a snack my cat loves.

2073
01:20:32,027 --> 01:20:33,628
GET READY TO LAUGH IN THE NEW YEAR

2074
01:20:35,530 --> 01:20:37,098
I never knew her eyes were so big.

2075
01:20:37,165 --> 01:20:39,634
It's the kind of flavor
every guy will love.

2076
01:20:39,868 --> 01:20:40,702
FIGURED OUT BH'S TASTE

2077
01:20:41,269 --> 01:20:44,206
Who won the opening game of 2026?

2078
01:20:47,275 --> 01:20:49,377
This is the class of chefs
of <i>Chef & My Fridge.</i>

2079
01:20:59,754 --> 01:21:04,759
Subtitle translation by: Eunsook Youn
